\rem /s1 Jerusalem Will Fall to Nebuchadrezzar; Warnings to kings and people; God Rejects Zedekiah's Request; No Deliverance from Babylon; Jerusalem's Defeat Is Predicted
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ313313 \add вүҲgave\add* Yirmeyah \add (Jeremiah)\add* a meesage when KingВҰ313316 Tsidkiyah \add (ZedekiahВҰ313317)\add* sentВҰ313314 Malkiyah'sВҰ313323 son PashhurВҰ313320 and Maaseyah'sВҰ313329 son Tsefanyah \add (ZephaniahВҰ313326)\add* the priestВҰ313330 to him, and they said,
\v 2 вҖңPlease \add вүҲrequest\add* Yahweh'sВҰ313339 advice on our behalf, becauseВҰ313340 the Babylonian KingВҰ313342 NebuchadnezzarВҰ313341 is \add вүҲattacking\add* us. Perhaps Yahweh will doВҰ313348 miracles for us like \add he has in the past\add*, and will make him \add вүҲstop attacking us and leave\add*.вҖқ\x + \xo 21:2: \xt 2Ki 25:1-11; 2Ch 36:17-21.\x*
