\m Listen, I'm aboutВҰ313374 to \add вүҲmake your own weaponsВҰ313377 ineffective\add* thatВҰ313379 you're all using to fightВҰ313383 the Babylonian kingВҰ313387 and the Babylonians \add (Heb. KasdiВҰ313391 = Chaldeans)\add* who are layingВҰ313392 siegeВҰ313392 to you from outsideВҰ313394 the wallВҰ313395, and I'llВҰ313396 gatherВҰ313396 them\f + \fr 21:4 \ft This last part of the sentence is left quite literal, as it's ambiguous in the Hebrew, what or who the вҖҳthemвҖҷ is referring to here.\f* in the middleВҰ313400 of this cityВҰ313401.
\v 5 ThenВҰ313404 IВҰ313405 myself will fightВҰ313404 you all \add вүҲwith all my strength and power\add* in my anger and rage and terrible fury,
\v 6 and I'llВҰ313416 \add вүҲkill\add* this city's inhabitantsВҰ313419вҖ”people and animals will all dieВҰ313430 in a \add вүҲterrible\add* plague.
\v 7 ThenВҰ313432 YahwehВҰ313437 declares that afterВҰ313432 that I'llВҰ313438 hand over Yehudah'sВҰ313444 King Tsidkiyah \add вүҲalong with\add* his officers, and the peopleВҰ313451 in this cityВҰ313455 who survive the plague and sword and famineВҰ313466, to the Babylonian King NebuchadnezzarВҰ313468, and to their enemiesВҰ313473 who \add вүҲwant to kill them\add*. He'll \add вүҲkill them with\add* the swordвҖ”he won'tВҰ313481 spare them or show pity or compassionВҰ313488.
\p
\v 8 ThenВҰ313490 you mustВҰ313494 tell this to the peopleВҰ313492:
\m YahwehВҰ313497 saysВҰ313496 that I'mВҰ313498 \add вүҲabout to give you the choice between\add* the path to lifeВҰ313504 andВҰ313490 the path to deathВҰ313508.
\v 9 AnyoneВҰ313510 who stays in this cityВҰ313511 will dieВҰ313513 from \add вүҲwar\add*, famineВҰ313515, or plague, butВҰ313515 anyoneВҰ313510 who goesВҰ313517 out and falls to their knees in front of the Babylonians who've surrounded you all, will live They'll escape with their lives \add that way\add*
\v 10 because I'veВҰ313533 \add вүҲalready decided\add* to harm this city \add вүҲrather than doing good\add*. YahwehВҰ313542 declares that \add @this city\add* will be \add вүҲhanded over\add* to the BabylonianВҰ313546 king and he'll burn it \add down\add*.
