\v 3 YahwehВҰ313657 says \add that you must\add* administer justiceВҰ313659 and \add вүҲdo what's rightВҰ313660\add*. Rescue anyoneВҰ313662 who's been robbedВҰ313662, from their oppressorВҰ313664. Don't mistreat any foreigner or orphan or widowВҰ313667. Don't be violentВҰ313673, and don'tВҰ313668 shed innocentВҰ313675 bloodВҰ313674 in this placeВҰ313679,
\v 4 because if you carefullyВҰ313685 do those thingsВҰ313689, then the kingsВҰ313695 who sit on David'sВҰ313697 throneВҰ313700 will enter through the gatesВҰ313692 of this palace riding in chariotsВҰ313702 or on horsesВҰ313703, \add вүҲalong with\add* their officials and their peopleВҰ313707.
\v 5 \add вүҲHoweverВҰ313717,\add* if you \add вүҲtake no notice\add* of those \add вүҲinstructions\add*, thenВҰ313709 YahwehВҰ313720 \add вүҲsolemnly promises\add* that this \add вүҲpalace\add* will becomeВҰ313724 a \add вүҲpile of rubbleВҰ313723\add*,\x + \xo 22:5: \xt Mat 23:28; Luk 13:35.\x*
