\p
\v 1 вҮ”After the Babylonian King NebuchadnezzarВҰ314986 had carried away Yehoyakin \add (Jehoiakim, Heb. Yekonyah = Jeconiah)\add*, son of Yehudah's King Yehoyakim \add (Jehoiakim)\add*, as well as Yehudah's officialsВҰ315001 and Yerushalem'sВҰ315009 craftsmenВҰ315005 and metalsmiths, and had taken them to BabylonВҰ314989, YahwehВҰ314975 showedВҰ314974 me twoВҰ314977 basketsВҰ314978 of figsВҰ314979 placed in frontВҰ314981 of \add *his\add* templeВҰ314982.\x + \xo 24:1: \xt 2Ki 24:12-16; 2Ch 36:10.\x*
\v 2 One basket of figs was very good like earlyВҰ315019, ripe figs, butВҰ315020 the figs in the other basket were so bad thatВҰ315025 they \add вүҲweren't edible\add*.
\v 3 Then YahwehВҰ315033 asked me, вҖңYirmeyah, what do you see?вҖқ
\p вҖңFigs,вҖқ I \add вүҲreplied\add*. вҖң\add Some\add* figs that \add вүҲlook\add* very good, and \add *others\add* that are so bad \add вүҲthey're inedible\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 4 Then YahwehВҰ315059 \add вүҲgave\add* me this messageВҰ315057:
\v 5 Yisrael's godВҰ315067, YahwehВҰ315066, saysВҰ315065 this: I'llВҰ315074 look favourably at the exiles from YehudahВҰ315078 just like those good figsВҰ315069, the exiles that I'veВҰ315080 sentВҰ315080 out from this placeВҰ315083 to Babylonia.
\v 6 I'll \add вүҲgive them my favour\add* and restore them to this land. I'll buildВҰ315098 them up, and not tear them down. I'll plantВҰ315101 them, and not uproot them.
\v 7 ThenВҰ315105 I will giveВҰ315105 them a \add вүҲdesire\add* to knowВҰ315108 me, becauseВҰ315110 I'm YahwehВҰ315112. They'll be my peopleВҰ315116 andВҰ315105 I will be theirВҰ315127 godВҰ315120, so they will turn to me \add вүҲwholeheartedly\add*.
\p
\v 8 \add вүҲButВҰ315130\add* YahwehВҰ315142 declares that \add just\add* like \add &those\add* bad figsВҰ315130 that are \add вүҲinedible\add* \add will be discarded\add*, I'llВҰ315144 act in that \add same\add* way towards Yehudah'sВҰ315150 KingВҰ315148 ZedekiahВҰ315147, along with his officialsВҰ315153 and the rest of YerushalemВҰ315157 who remainВҰ315158 in this land or go to stay in the land of EgyptВҰ315163.
\v 9 I'll turn them into something horrifyingвҖ”a disaster, \add right thereВҰ315182\add* in the sight of all the world's kingdomsВҰ315170вҖ”a disgrace and a subject for proverbs, tauntsВҰ315174, and cursesВҰ315175 in every placeВҰ315178 that I'll drive them into.
\v 10 I'llВҰ315184 sendВҰ315184 \add вүҲarmies\add*, famineВҰ315191, and \add вүҲdisease\add* against them untilВҰ315195 they're destroyed from the land thatВҰ315200 I gaveВҰ315202 to them and theirВҰ315204 ancestorsВҰ315204.
\c 25
\s1 Exile to Babylon foretold
\rem /s1 Seventy Years of Captivity; The Babylonian Captivity Foretold; The Enemy from the North
\p
\v 1 This is the messageВҰ315207 thatВҰ315208 came to Yirmeyah \add (Jeremiah)\add* concerning all the peopleВҰ315218 of Yehudah \add (Judah)\add* in the fourthВҰ315221 year of \add the reign of\add* Yehoyakim (\add Jehoiakim,\add* son of Yehudah'sВҰ315219 King Yoshiyah \add (Josiah)\add*), whichВҰ315208 was the firstВҰ315230 year of \add the reign of\add* the Babylonian King NebuchadnezzarВҰ315231.
\v 2 The prophetВҰ315238 Yirmeyah proclaimed this to all the peopleВҰ315243 \add вүҲacross\add* YehudahВҰ315244 \add вүҲincludingВҰ315245\add* all of Yerushalem'sВҰ315249 inhabitantsВҰ315248, saying:
\v 3 вҮ”Yahweh's messagesВҰ315272 have been coming to me for twenty-three years since the thirteenth year of the reign of Yehudah'sВҰ315262 king Yoshiyah (\add Josiah,\add* Amon'sВҰ315260 son), and I'veВҰ315276 \add вүҲpassed them on\add* to you all \add вүҲover and over again\add*, \add вүҲbutВҰ315263\add* you haven't \add вүҲtaken any notice\add* \add of them\add*.
\v 4 YahwehВҰ315284 sentВҰ315283 all his servantsВҰ315290 the prophetsВҰ315291 to you again andВҰ315283 again, butВҰ315283 you all haven't listenedВҰ315295 \add вүҲor paid any attention\add*.
\v 5 \add вүЎThose prophets\add* said, вҖҳLet everyoneВҰ315308 turnВҰ315305 from their wickedВҰ315311 ways and their evilВҰ315310 activities, and return to the land thatВҰ315317 YahwehВҰ315319 gaveВҰ315318 in ancient times to your ancestorsВҰ315321 and to all of you as a permanentВҰ315327 \add inheritance\add*.
\v 6 \add вүҲSoВҰ315345\add* don't walkВҰ315331 afterВҰ315332 otherВҰ315334 godsВҰ315333 to worshipВҰ315336 them or to bow down to them, and don't provokeВҰ315340 \add %him\add* with \add вүҲthings you make with\add* yourВҰ315343 handsВҰ315343, and thenВҰ315329 \add %he\add* won'tВҰ315329 harm you all.вҖҷ
\v 7 \add вүҲButВҰ315348\add* YahwehВҰ315354 declares that you all haven't listenedВҰ315350 to me, \add вүҲbecause with what you've made\add*, you've provokedВҰ315356 me to do harm to you.
\p
\v 8 So Commander-in-chief YahwehВҰ315367 saysВҰ315366 this: Since all of you haven't listenВҰ315373 to my messages,
\v 9 listen, I'm about to sendВҰ315379 out a command to fetchВҰ315380 all the northernВҰ315386 peoples. YahwehВҰ315389 declares that I will bringВҰ315397 my servantВҰ315396, the Babylonian KingВҰ315393 NebuchadnezzarВҰ315392 and \add his armies\add* against this land and itsВҰ315404 inhabitantsВҰ315404, and against all the nationsВҰ315408 around you. I will \add вүҲmark\add* them for destructionВҰ315411 and turn them into a horrorвҖ”\add вүҲsomething to be hissed at\add*, and permanentВҰ315416 ruinsВҰ315415.
\v 10 I'llВҰ315418 put an end to the sounds of gladnessВҰ315423 and \add вүҲcelebration\add*, the sounds of \add #brides\add* and \add #grooms\add*, \add and\add* the sound of the millstones and the lightВҰ315430 of the lamp.\x + \xo 25:10: a \xt Jer 7:34; 16:9; \xo b \xt Rev 18:22-23.\x*
\v 11 ThenВҰ315433 all of this land will becomeВҰ315433 a desolationВҰ315438 and a horror, and theseВҰ315442 nationsВҰ315441 will serveВҰ315440 the BabylonianВҰ315446 kingВҰ315445 for seventyВҰ315447 years.\x + \xo 25:11: \xt 2Ch 36:21; Jer 29:10; Dan 9:2.\x*
\p
\v 12 ThenВҰ315450 after seventyВҰ315452 years have \add вүҲpassed\add*, thenВҰ315450 I'llВҰ315454 punish the kingВҰ315457 of BabylonВҰ315459 and that nationВҰ315462вҖ”the landВҰ315472 of the ChaldeansвҖ”for theirВҰ315469 wickedness, and makeВҰ315474 it into a permanentВҰ315477 wasteland. That is Yahweh'sВҰ315466 declaration.
\v 13 ThenВҰ315479 I'llВҰ315479 carry out all the messages that I'd spokenВҰ315492 against that land, andВҰ315479 everythingВҰ315495 writtenВҰ315497 in this document that Yirmeyah has prophesiedВҰ315502 against all the nationsВҰ315508.
\v 14 \add вүҲYes\add* many other nations and greatВҰ315520 kingsВҰ315519 will also make slaves out of those nations. I'llВҰ315521 repayВҰ315521 them for \add вүҲeverything they've done\add*.
\s1 The punishment of God of nations
\rem /s1 The Cup of God's Wrath; God's Judgment on the Nations; The Cup of the Lord's Anger
\p
\v 15 \add вүҲYes\add* Yisrael's godВҰ315532 YahwehВҰ315531 told me, вҖңTake this cup of the wine of fury from my handВҰ315542, and all the nationsВҰ315549 thatВҰ315550 I'm sendingВҰ315552 you to, makeВҰ315543 them drinkВҰ315543 it.
\v 16 They'll drinkВҰ315556 and thenВҰ315556 staggerВҰ315557 around and actВҰ315558 like mad \add >people\add* \add вүҲwhen they see the deadly army\add* thatВҰ315561 I'm sending out to them.
\p
\v 17 \add вүҲSoВҰ315566\add* I tookВҰ315566 the cup from Yahweh'sВҰ315571 handВҰ315570 andВҰ315566 madeВҰ315572 all the nationsВҰ315577 thatВҰ315578 \add *he'd\add* sentВҰ315580 me to, drinkВҰ315572 from it,
\v 18 \add as well as\add* Yehudah'sВҰ315590 citiesВҰ315589 \add вүҲincludingВҰ315587\add* YerushalemВҰ315586 and its \add #king\add* and officialsВҰ315596вҖ”to turn them into ruins and something terrifying, and into \add вүҲsomething to hiss and curseВҰ315602 at\add*, as they are until this present dayВҰ315603.
\v 19 \add Those nations included:\add*
\li1 Egypt'sВҰ315611 KingВҰ315609 Far'oh \add (PharaohВҰ315608)\add*, his officialsВҰ315617, his leaders, and all his peopleВҰ315622,
\li1
\v 20 all people of mixed heritage and all the kings of the land of Uts,
\li1 all the kings of the land of Philistia: AshkelonВҰ315642, Azzah \add (GazaВҰ315645)\add*, EkronВҰ315648, and the remnantВҰ315650 from AshdodВҰ315651,
\li1
\v 21 EdomВҰ315655, Moav, and the Ammonites,
\li1
\v 22 all the kings of Tsor \add (TyreВҰ315669)\add* andВҰ315664 Tsidon \add (SidonВҰ315674)\add*,
\li1 the kings from the coastlandsВҰ315677 across the sea,
\li1
\v 23 DedanВҰ315684, TemaВҰ315687, BuzВҰ315690,
\li1 andВҰ315682 all who cutВҰ315694 the cornersВҰ315695 \add of their hair\add*,
\li1
\v 24 all the ArabianВҰ315701 kings,
\li1 andВҰ315697 all the kings of the mixedВҰ315706 tribes who live in the desert,
\li1
\v 25 all the kings from ZimriВҰ315715, ElamВҰ315720, andВҰ315710 MediaВҰ315725,
\li1
\v 26 all the kingsВҰ315731 of the northВҰ315732, both near andВҰ315727 far, one after another,
\li1 all the kingdomsВҰ315742 \add вүҲaround the world\add*.
\p And after all of them, the Babylonian\f + \fr 25:26 \ft вҖҳBabylonвҖҷ here in the Hebrew is вҖҳSheshakвҖҷ, which is Hebrew for вҖҳBabylonвҖҷ with the letters substituted in a simple code.\f* kingВҰ315749 will drinkВҰ315751 \add it too\add*.
\p
\v 27 ThenВҰ315754 Yahweh told me to tell them, вҖҳYisrael's godВҰ315762, Commander-in-chief Yahweh, saysВҰ315759 this: Drink and becomeВҰ315765 drunkВҰ315765, thenВҰ315754 vomitВҰ315766, fallВҰ315767 down, and don'tВҰ315768 get up \add again\add* \add вүҲuntil the deadly army arrives\add* thatВҰ315772 I'm sending among you.вҖҷ
\v 28 ThenВҰ315777 if any \add of the above\add* refuseВҰ315779 to take the cup from your handВҰ315783 to drink, tell me, вҖҳCommander-in-chief YahwehВҰ315789 says that you certainlyВҰ315791 mustВҰ315779 drink it,
\v 29 because listen, I'm about to bring disaster to the cityВҰ315796 thatВҰ315797 is calledВҰ315798 by my nameВҰ315800, and should you yourselves be free from punishment? You won'tВҰ315808 be free, because I'm callingВҰ315813 a \add вүҲdeadly army\add* against all the inhabitantsВҰ315818 of the land.вҖҷ
\m That is Commander-in-chief Yahweh'sВҰ315821 declaration.
\p
\v 30 You mustВҰ315825 prophesyВҰ315825 all theseВҰ315831 messages against them, telling them:
\q1 вҖҳYahwehВҰ315834 will roar from the heights
\q1 and he'll \add вүҲshout\add* with his voiceВҰ315840 from his sacredВҰ315838 residence,
\q1 and he will roar mightilyВҰ315841 against his \add вүҲland\add*,
\q1 and he will shout, like those who treadВҰ315847 \add grapes in a wine-pressing pit\add*
\q1 against all those who live on the earthВҰ315853.
\q1
\v 31 The uproarВҰ315856 will \add вүҲbe heard even at\add* the ends of the earthВҰ315860
\q1 becauseВҰ315861 YahwehВҰ315863 brings a charge against the nationsВҰ315864.
\q1 He \add вүҲwill pass\add* judgment on all humankind
\q1 and \add вүҲhave the wickedВҰ315870 killed in war\add*.
\m That is Yahweh'sВҰ315863 declaration.
\p
\v 32 Commander-in-chief says this:
\q1 Listen, disaster is spreading from nation to nation.
\q1 A \add вүҲterrible\add* stormВҰ315889 is rising from the ends of the earthВҰ315894.
\m
\v 33 ThenВҰ315896 thoseВҰ315897 killed that dayВҰ315899 by YahwehВҰ315898 will be spread from \add one\add* end of the earth to the other. They won'tВҰ315907 be mournedВҰ315908 \add over\add*, gatheredВҰ315910, or buriedВҰ315912вҖ”they'll be like dung lying on the ground.
\p
\v 34 Wail, \add you\add* shepherdsВҰ315921, and call out for help.
\q1 Roll around in the dust, \add you\add* leaders of the flockВҰ315925,
\q1 becauseВҰ315926 the \add вүҲtimeВҰ315929\add* has come for your slaughterВҰ315930.
\q1 You'll all be scattered when you fallВҰ315932, like \add fragments of broken\add* pottery.
\q1
\v 35 There's no safe placeВҰ315937 for the shepherdsВҰ315940 \add to go to\add*.
\q1 вүҲThere'll be no escape for the leaders of the flockВҰ315943.
\q1
\v 36 Hear the shepherds' cries of distrressВҰ315946
\q1 вүҲandВҰ315948 the wails of the leaders of the flockВҰ315950,
\q1 вҶ’because YahwehВҰ315954 is destroyingВҰ315953 theirВҰ315957 \add #pastures\add*.
\q1
\v 37 SoВҰ315959 the peacefulВҰ315961 pasturesВҰ315960 will be devastatedВҰ315959
\q1 \add вүҲbecause of\add* Yahweh'sВҰ315966 \add вүҲfierce\add* angerВҰ315964.
\q1
\v 38 He's left his den like a young lion would,
\q1 becauseВҰ315979 theirВҰ315974 land will becomeВҰ315973 a horror
\q1 due to the oppressor'sВҰ315978 anger and \add @Yahweh's\add* fierce angry.
\c 26
\s1 Wanting a death sentence for Yirmeyah
\rem /s1 Jeremiah's Prophecies in the Temple; Jeremiah Threatened With Death; Jeremiah Is Brought to Trial; Jeremiah's Escape from Death
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲNear\add* the beginningВҰ315984 of the reign of Yehoyakim \add (Jehoiakim, Yoshiyah's\add*/Josiah's son), this messageВҰ315993 cameВҰ315992 from YahwehВҰ315996:
\v 2 YahwehВҰ316002 says this: Stand in the courtyardВҰ316004 of my \add вүҲtemple\add* and speak about all of Yehudah'sВҰ316014 citiesВҰ316013 who come to worshipВҰ316016 at my \add вүҲresidence\add*. Proclaim all the messagesВҰ316031 thatВҰ316024 I've commandedВҰ316025 you to say to themвҖ”don'tВҰ316028 hold \add вүҲanything\add* back.
\v 3 Maybe they'll listenВҰ316034 and everyoneВҰ316036 will turn from \add #their wicked ways\add*, and then I would turn back the disaster thatВҰ316043 I'm planningВҰ316045 to \add вүҲsend\add* to them because of their wicked \add вүҲbehaviour\add*,
\v 4 \add вүҲso\add* you \add need to\add* tell them that YahwehВҰ316056 saysВҰ316055 this:
\m If you don'tВҰ316059 listenВҰ316060 to me so as to \add вүҲfollow my instructions that I'veВҰ316065 given to\add* you all,
\v 5 \add вүЎif you don'tВҰ316080\add* listenВҰ316068 to the wordsВҰ316071 of my servantsВҰ316072 the prophetsВҰ316073 that I'veВҰ316075 been \add regularly\add* sending to you, and \add indeed\add* you haven't listenedВҰ316081,
\v 6 thenВҰ316083 I'll \add вүҲdestroy\add* this houseВҰ316086 like \add I did at\add* ShilohВҰ316088\x + \xo 26:6: \xt Josh 18:1; Psa 78:60; Jer 7:12-14.\x* andВҰ316083 I'll turn this cityВҰ316091 into a curseВҰ316095 to/for all the nationsВҰ316097 \add вүҲin the world\add*.
\p
\v 7 The priestsВҰ316102, the prophetsВҰ316103, and all the peopleВҰ316106 heardВҰ316101 Yirmeyah proclaiming those wordsВҰ316113 at Yahweh'sВҰ316116 \add вүҲtemple\add*.
\v 8 ThenВҰ316118 as soon as YirmeyahВҰ316121 had finishedВҰ316120 saying everything that YahwehВҰ316129 had commandedВҰ316128 him to tell all the people, the priestsВҰ316138 and the prophetsВҰ316139 and all the people seizedВҰ316136 him \add вүҲand threatened to kill him, saying\add*:
\v 9 Why have youВҰ316148 prophesiedВҰ316148 in Yahweh's nameВҰ316149 and said that this \add вүҲtemple\add* will be \add destroyed\add* like ShilohВҰ316153, and that this cityВҰ316157 will become desolateВҰ316159, with no \add #inhabitants\add*?вҖқ Then all the peopleВҰ316165 \add вүҲgathered together\add* against Yirmeyah at Yahweh's \add вүҲresidence\add*.
\p
\v 10 ThenВҰ316172 Yehudah'sВҰ316175 officialsВҰ316174 heardВҰ316172 \add вүҲabout what was going on\add*, andВҰ316172 they wentВҰ316179 up from the \add вүҲpalace\add* to \add вүҲthe temple where\add* they sat in the gateway at the New Gate at Yahweh'sВҰ316184 \add вүҲresidence\add*.
\v 11 Then the priestsВҰ316194 and the prophets spoke to the officialsВҰ316198 and to all the peopleВҰ316203, saying, вҖңIt's right for this manВҰ316208 to die, becauseВҰ316210 he prophesiedВҰ316211 againstВҰ316212 this cityВҰ316214, as you've all heardВҰ316217 with your own earsВҰ316218.вҖқ
\p
\v 12 \add вүҲSoВҰ316220\add* YirmeyahВҰ316221 spoke to all the officialsВҰ316226 and all the peopleВҰ316231 and saidВҰ316220, вҖңYahwehВҰ316233 has sentВҰ316234 me out to prophesyВҰ316235 to sayВҰ316232 all the wordsВҰ316247 thatВҰ316248 you have heardВҰ316249, againstВҰ316236 \add both\add* this \add вүҲtemple\add* and this cityВҰ316242.
\v 13 \add вүҲSoВҰ316251 now,\add* improve your waysВҰ316253 and your \add вүҲpractices\add*, and listenВҰ316255 to the voiceВҰ316256 of your godВҰ316258 YahwehВҰ316257 so that he'll relent concerningВҰ316261 the disaster that he's proclaimed against you all.
\v 14 \add вүҲAs for me,\add* here I am in your \add #hands\add*вҖ”doВҰ316271 to me \add вүҲwhatever you think\add* is rightВҰ316275 andВҰ316268 proper.
\v 15 \add вүҲHowever,\add* you mustВҰ316281 surely know that if you kill me, then you're all bringing innocentВҰ316291 bloodВҰ316290 on yourselvesВҰ316294 and on this cityВҰ316297 and its inhabitantsВҰ316301, becauseВҰ316282 YahwehВҰ316305 has truly sent me to you to proclaim all theseВҰ316313 messages for you all \add вүҲto hear\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 16 Then the officialsВҰ316317 and all the peopleВҰ316320 saidВҰ316316 to the priestsВҰ316323 and to the prophetsВҰ316326, вҖңThis manВҰ316329 \add вүҲdoesn't deserve to be sentencedВҰ316331 to\add* deathВҰ316333, becauseВҰ316334 he's spokenВҰ316338 to us in the nameВҰ316335 of ourВҰ316337 godВҰ316337, YahwehВҰ316336.вҖқ
\p
\v 17 ThenВҰ316341 \add вүҲsome\add* of \add Yehudah's\add* eldersВҰ316343 \add вүҲstepped forward\add* andВҰ316341 spoke to all the peopleВҰ316351 who were gathered there,
\v 18 вҖңMicah (\add Heb. Mikah,\add* the Morashtite) prophesiedВҰ316358 \add вүҲduring the lifetime\add* of Yehudah'sВҰ316363 KingВҰ316361 Hizkiyah\add (Hezekiah)\add*, and he told all the peopleВҰ316369 from Yehudah that Commander-in-chief YahwehВҰ316376 saysВҰ316374 this:
\q1 TsiyyonВҰ316378 \add (ZionВҰ316378)\add*, a fieldВҰ316379 will be ploughed,
\q1 and YerushalemВҰ316381 will become heapsВҰ316382 \add of ruinsВҰ316382\add*,
\q1 and the \add вүҲtemple\add* hillВҰ316384 will become an \add вүҲovergrown\add* forestВҰ316387.\x + \xo 26:18: \xt Mic 3:12.\x*
\m
\v 19 Did Yehudah'sВҰ316394 KingВҰ316392 Hizkiyah or anyone else in Yehudah put him to death? Didn't \add @Hizkiyah\add* \add вүҲrespect and honour\add* Yahweh and \add вүҲask for\add* \add *his\add* favour, and didn'tВҰ316398 Yahweh \add вүҲrelent from sending\add* the disaster that he had pronounced against them? \add вүҲIt seems that\add* we're aboutВҰ316418 to bring greatВҰ316420 \add вүҲharm\add* on ourselves.вҖқ
\p
\v 20 \add вүҲNow\add* there was \add вүҲanother\add* manВҰ316427 prophesyingВҰ316429 in Yahweh'sВҰ316431 nameВҰ316430 of Yahweh: Uriyah (son of ShemayahВҰ316435 from Kiriat-Yearim) who prophesiedВҰ316438 against this cityВҰ316441 andВҰ316425 against this land \add вүҲwith similar\add* messages to Yirmeyah.
\v 21 \add вүҲWhenВҰ316451\add* KingВҰ316452 Yehoyakim \add (Jehoiakim)\add* and all his warriorsВҰ316457 and all the officialsВҰ316460 heard his wordsВҰ316463, the king \add вүҲwanted\add* to put him to deathВҰ316466. \add вүҲHowever when\add* Uriyah heard \add >about it\add*, he became afraidВҰ316469, and he fled and went to EgyptВҰ316472 \add (Heb. Mitsrayim)\add*.
\v 22 \add вүҲHowever,\add* KingВҰ316475 Yehoyakim sent sent Akbor's son ElnatanВҰ316480 andВҰ316474 several other men to EgyptВҰ316478 \add to get Uriyah\add*.
\v 23 They broughtВҰ316490 Uriyah back from EgyptВҰ316494 and tookВҰ316495 him to KingВҰ316498 Yehoyakim \add вүҲwho ran him through with a swordВҰ316501\add* and threwВҰ316502 his corpseВҰ316505 into the \add вүҲpublic graveyardВҰ316508\add*.
\p
\v 24 However, Shafan'sВҰ316517 son AhikamВҰ316514 \add вүҲsupported\add* Yirmeyah and \add вүҲdidn'tВҰ316522 allow the peopleВҰ316528 to kill himВҰ316529\add*.
\c 27
\s1 Yirmeyah wears a yoke
\rem /s1 Jeremiah opposes false prophets; The Sign of the Yoke; Jeremiah Wears an Ox Yoke; Judah to Serve Nebuchadnezzar
\p
\v 1 At the beginningВҰ316532 of the reignВҰ316533 of Yehudah'sВҰ316539 KingВҰ316538 Yehoyakim (\add Jehoiakim\add*, son of Yoshiyah \add Josiah\add*), this messageВҰ316541 cameВҰ316540 to Yirmeyah \add (Jeremiah)\add* from YahwehВҰ316547,\x + \xo 27:1: \xt 2Ki 24:18-20; 2Ch 36:11-13.\x*
\v 2 telling \add %him\add* this:
\m MakeВҰ316553 yourselfВҰ316556 a wooden \add ox\add* yoke with bars, and \add вүҲtie\add* it to yourВҰ316562 neck.
\v 3 \add вүҲUse it to sendВҰ316564 messages\add* to the kings of EdomВҰ316568, MoabВҰ316572, AmmonВҰ316577, Tsor \add (TyreВҰ316581)\add*, andВҰ316564 Tsidon \add (SidonВҰ316585)\add*, \add вүҲthrough the ambassadors\add* \add from those countries\add* who've come to YerushalemВҰ316589 to \add meet with\add* KingВҰ316567 Tsidkiyah \add (ZedekiahВҰ316592)\add*
\v 4 to tell them that Yisrael'sВҰ316608 godВҰ316607, Commander-in-chief YahwehВҰ316605 says to give theirВҰ316600 masters this message:
\v 5 I myself madeВҰ316616 the earth \add and\add* the \add #people\add* and \add #animals\add* thatВҰ316626 are on the earth, by my \add вүҲdirect actions\add* and my greatВҰ316632 strength, and I giveВҰ316635 it to whoever \add вүҲsee fit\add*.
\v 6 Now I've \add вүҲpersonally handed over\add* all theseВҰ316648 landsВҰ316647 to my servantВҰ316654, the Babylonian KingВҰ316651 NebuchadnezzarВҰ316650, andВҰ316640 I've also given the animalsВҰ316658 in the countrysideВҰ316659 to him to serveВҰ316662 him.
\v 7 All the nations will serve him and his son and then his \add вүҲgrandson\add*, untilВҰ316677 the time of his own landВҰ316681 comesВҰ316678 \add due\add*. \add вүҲYes, it will\add*, and then many nations and greatВҰ316690 kingsВҰ316689 will make him serve them.
\p
\v 8 Any nation or kingdomВҰ316694 that won't serveВҰ316698 the Babylonian King Nebuchadnezzar and that won't put its neck into his yoke, thenВҰ316692 I'llВҰ316720 punish that nation with \add вүҲwar\add* and famineВҰ316718 and \add вүҲdisease\add* untilВҰ316728 I'veВҰ316730 used \add @King Nebuchadnezzar\add* to finish them \add off\add*. That is Yahweh'sВҰ316727 declaration,
\v 9 \add вүҲso\add* don'tВҰ316735 you all keep listeningВҰ316737 to your вҖҳprophetsВҰ316740вҖҷ, and to your divinersВҰ316743 and dreamersВҰ316745, and to your soothsayersВҰ316748 and sorcerersВҰ316751вҖ”all those who keep telling you that you all won'tВҰ316735 serveВҰ316759 the BabylonianВҰ316763 kingВҰ316762,
\v 10 because they're prophesyingВҰ316768 lies to you, so as to removeВҰ316771 you all far away from on your land. \add вүҲYes,\add* I will driveВҰ316775 you all out and you'll die \add in a foreign land\add*.
\v 11 \add вүҲHowever,\add* the nation that bringsВҰ316781 its neck into the Babylonian king's yoke and servesВҰ316789 him, I'llВҰ316790 let \add @that nation\add* remainВҰ316790 on its landВҰ316793, and it will cultivate it and live \add вүҲthere\add*. That's is Yahweh'sВҰ316796 declaration.
\p
\v 12 ThenВҰ316801 to Yehudah'sВҰ316806 KingВҰ316804 Tsidkiyah \add (ZedekiahВҰ316803)\add*, I \add вүҲpassed on\add* those \add same\add* wordsВҰ316810, saying, вҖңPut your necksВҰ316816 into the yoke of the Babylonian king, and serveВҰ316821 him and his peopleВҰ316823, and live.
\v 13 Why would youВҰ316828 and yourВҰ316829 peopleВҰ316829 dieВҰ316827 from \add вүҲwar\add*, famineВҰ316831, and \add вүҲdisease\add*, as YahwehВҰ316835 has \add вүҲsaid will come to any\add* nationВҰ316838 thatВҰ316839 doesn't serveВҰ316842 the Babylonian kingВҰ316845?
\v 14 \add вүҲSoВҰ316848\add* don'tВҰ316848 listenВҰ316850 to the messages from the prophets who are speaking to you when they tell you all not to serveВҰ316859 the kingВҰ316862 of BabylonВҰ316863 as they're prophesyingВҰ316867 lies to you
\v 15 because I didn'tВҰ316871 send them. YahwehВҰ316875 declares that they're using my nameВҰ316878 to prophesy lies so that I'll driveВҰ316881 you out, and you'll all perishВҰ316883вҖ”\add both\add* you and the prophets who are prophesying to you.вҖқ
\v 16 ThenВҰ316889 I told the priestsВҰ316891 and all those peopleВҰ316896 that Yahweh saysВҰ316901: Don'tВҰ316903 listenВҰ316905 to the wordsВҰ316908 of your prophets who are prophesying to you and saying that the utensils from Yahweh'sВҰ316902 \add вүҲtemple\add* will \add вүҲsoon\add* be broughtВҰ316918 back from BabylonВҰ316919, becauseВҰ316922 they're prophesying lies to you.
\v 17 Don'tВҰ316928 listenВҰ316930 to them. Serve the Babylonian kingВҰ316935 andВҰ316938 liveВҰ316938. Why should this cityВҰ316941 becomeВҰ316940 a ruinВҰ316943?
\v 18 If theyВҰ316948 were prophetsВҰ316947 \add вүҲwho really have access to\add* Yahweh's messageВҰ316952, thenВҰ316945 pleaseВҰ316958 let them intercede with Commander-in-chief Yahweh so thatВҰ316966 the utensils remainingВҰ316966 in Yahweh's \add вүҲtemple\add* and in Yehudah'sВҰ316972 king's \add вүҲpalace\add* and in YerushalemВҰ316973 \add вүҲdon'tВҰ316961 end up being taken\add* to BabylonВҰ316974.
\p
\v 19 \add вүҲYes,\add* Commander-in-chief YahwehВҰ316980 has spoken about the \add bronze\add* pillarsВҰ316984 and the \add large, bronze\add* \add вүҲwater basin\add*, and concerningВҰ316982 the \add bronze\add* standsВҰ316990 and the rest of the utensils remainingВҰ316992 in this cityВҰ316995,
\v 20 which the Babylonian King NebuchadnezzarВҰ317002 didn'tВҰ316999 take when he exiledВҰ317005 Yehudah'sВҰ317015 King Yekonyah (\add Jeconiah,\add* son of \add Yehoyakim/\add*Jehoiakim) from Yerushalem to BabylonВҰ317004, along with all the noblesВҰ317021 of Yehudah includingВҰ317018 Yerushalem.
\v 21 Yisrael's godВҰ317031, Commander-in-chief Yahweh saysВҰ317028 about the utensils remainingВҰ317036 in Yahweh'sВҰ317029 \add вүҲtemple\add* and in the \add вүҲpalace\add* of the kingВҰ317040 of YehudahВҰ317042 and YerushalemВҰ317043:
\v 22 They'll be takenВҰ317046 to Babylon and they'll remainВҰ317048 thereВҰ317047 untilВҰ317049 the \add вүҲtime when I punish\add* \add @those Babylonians\add*, and then I'llВҰ317056 bring them \add вүҲback\add* and restore them to this placeВҰ317060. That is Yahweh'sВҰ317055 declaration.
\c 28
\s1 Yirmeyah vs Prophet Hananyah
\rem /s1 Jeremiah Condemns Hananiah; The False Prophet Hananiah; Jeremiah and the Prophet Hananiah; Hananiah Opposes Jeremiah and Dies
\p
\v 1 In the fifthВҰ317078 monthВҰ317077 of the fourthВҰ317076 year of the reignВҰ317069 of Yehudah'sВҰ317073 KingВҰ317071 Tsidkiyah \add (ZedekiahВҰ317070)\add*, Azzur'sВҰ317084 son HananyahВҰ317081 who was a вҖҳprophetВҰ317085вҖҷ from GibeonВҰ317087, said to me in Yahweh'sВҰ317089 \add вүҲtemple\add* as priestsВҰ317091 and all the peopleВҰ317094 \add watched\add*, saying,\x + \xo 28:1: \xt 2Ki 24:18-20; 2Ch 36:11-13.\x*
\v 2 вҖңYisrael's godВҰ317102, Commander-in-chief YahwehВҰ317100 saysВҰ317099: I've broken the yoke of the Babylonian kingВҰ317109.
\v 3 Within two yearsВҰ317114, I, myself, will bringВҰ317117 back here all the utensils from Yahweh'sВҰ317128 residence thatВҰ317129 the Babylonian KingВҰ317133 NebuchadnezzarВҰ317131 got from this place and took to BabylonВҰ317135.
\v 4 I, myself, will \add вүҲalso\add* bringВҰ317161 Yekonyah (\add Jeconiah,\add* the son of Yehudah'sВҰ317151 KingВҰ317149 Yehoyakim/\add Jehoiakim\add*) back to this placeВҰ317164, andВҰ317143 all the exilesВҰ317156 from Yehudah that were taken to BabylonВҰ317159, becauseВҰ317169 I'llВҰ317160 breakВҰ317170 the yoke of the Babylonian king. That is Yahweh'sВҰ317168 declaration.вҖқ
\p
\v 5 ThenВҰ317177 the prophet YirmeyahВҰ317178 spoke to the prophet HananyahВҰ317182, as the priestsВҰ317185 andВҰ317186 all the peopleВҰ317189 standingВҰ317190 in Yahweh'sВҰ317192 \add вүҲtemple\add* \add вүҲwatched\add*,
\v 6 saying, вҖңLet it be soвҖ”may Yahweh doВҰ317199 all that. May Yahweh \add вүҲconfirm\add* yourВҰ317205 messages that youВҰ317207 prophesiedВҰ317196, to bringВҰ317208 the \add вүҲtemple utensils\add* back to this placeВҰ317219, along with all the exilesВҰ317215 from BabylonВҰ317216.
\v 7 However, pleaseВҰ317226 listen to this messageВҰ317227 thatВҰ317229 I, myself, am speakingВҰ317231 \add вүҲas you and all the peopleВҰ317236 listen\add*:
\v 8 The prophets who \add вүҲpreceded\add* \add both\add* me and youВҰ317242, prophesiedВҰ317246 \add вүҲlong ago\add* that many \add вүҲnations\add* and powerful kingdomsВҰ317253 would experience wars, \add вүҲterrible suffering\add*, and \add вүҲdeadly diseases\add*.
\v 9 The prophet who prophesiesВҰ317261 about peaceВҰ317262, \add &that\add* prophet will be known as вҖҳa truthfulВҰ317272 prophet sentВҰ317270 by YahwehВҰ317271вҖҷ \add only\add* when his messageВҰ317264 comesВҰ317263 \add to pass\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 10 ThenВҰ317274 the prophet HananyahВҰ317275 tookВҰ317274 the yoke bar off the prophet Yirmeyah'sВҰ317282 neck, andВҰ317274 brokeВҰ317284 it.
\v 11 Then as all the peopleВҰ317291 watched, he saidВҰ317286, вҖңThis is what YahwehВҰ317295 saysВҰ317294: Just like that, I'llВҰ317297 breakВҰ317297 the yoke of the Babylonian KingВҰ317303 NebuchadnezzarВҰ317302 off the neck of all the nationsВҰ317314 within twoВҰ317307 more yearsВҰ317307.вҖқ
\p Then the prophetВҰ317317 Yirmeyah \add вүҲleft the gathering\add*.
\p
\v 12 вҮ”After the prophet HananyahВҰ317330 brokeВҰ317329 the yoke bar that had been on the prophet Yirmeyah's neck, Yahweh'sВҰ317324 messageВҰ317322 came to Yirmeyah saying,
\v 13 вҖңGo and tell HananyahВҰ317345 this: вҖҳYahwehВҰ317349 saysВҰ317348 that you'veВҰ317352 brokenВҰ317352 wooden yoke bars, butВҰ317342 in theirВҰ317354 placeВҰ317354, you'll makeВҰ317353 yoke bars out of iron,вҖҷ
\v 14 because Yisrael's godВҰ317364, Commander-in-chief YahwehВҰ317362 saysВҰ317361, вҖҳI've put an iron yoke bar on the neck of all theseВҰ317376 nationsВҰ317375 to serve the Babylonian KingВҰ317381 NebuchadnezzarВҰ317380, and they will \add indeed\add* serve him. I've also givenВҰ317390 him the animalsВҰ317388 from the countrysideВҰ317389.вҖҷ вҖқ
\p
\v 15 ThenВҰ317393 the prophet Yirmeyah told the prophet Hananyah, вҖңListen, pleaseВҰ317402, Hananyah. YahwehВҰ317407 hasn't sentВҰ317406 you, andВҰ317393 you yourself have madeВҰ317409 this peopleВҰ317412 \add group\add* \add вүҲput their trust in things that aren'tВҰ317404 true\add*.
\v 16 Because of that, Yahweh saysВҰ317420 this: вҖҳListen, I'm \add вүҲremoving you from this world\add*. \add вүҲYou'll dieВҰ317429 this very\add* yearВҰ317427, becauseВҰ317430 you have \add вүҲsaid things that would cause the people to rebelВҰ317432\add* againstВҰ317434 Yahweh.вҖҷ вҖқ
\p
\v 17 The prophetВҰ317440 HananyahВҰ317439 thenВҰ317438 diedВҰ317438 in the seventhВҰ317444 monthВҰ317443 of that yearВҰ317441.
\c 29
\s1 Yirmeyah's letter to the exiled Jews
\rem /s1 Jeremiah's Letter to the Exiles in Babylon; Jeremiah's Letter to the Jews in Babylonia
\p
\v 1 The prophet Yirmeyah sentВҰ317451 a \add вүҲletterВҰ317449\add* from Yerushalem to the remainderВҰ317457 of the eldersВҰ317458 of the exile, and to the priestsВҰ317462, and to the prophets, and to all the peopleВҰ317470 thatВҰ317450 NebuchadnezzarВҰ317473 had exiled from Yerushalem to BabylonВҰ317475\x + \xo 29:1-2: \xt 2Ki 24:12-16; 2Ch 36:10.\x*
\v 2 after the \add вүҲremoval\add* from Yerushalem of KingВҰ317481 Yekonyah \add (Jeconiah)\add* and the queenВҰ317482 mother, the \add вүҲcourtВҰ317483 officialsВҰ317484\add* and the leaders of YehudahВҰ317485 and Yerushalem, plusВҰ317482 the craftsmenВҰ317487 and the metalsmiths.
\v 3 \add He sent it\add* with Shafan'sВҰ317495 son ElasahВҰ317492 and Hilkiyah's son GemaryahВҰ317496, who Yehudah'sВҰ317505 King Tsidkiyah \add (ZedekiahВҰ317502)\add* sent to the Babylonian King NebuchadnezzarВҰ317508 in BabylonВҰ317510. \add The letter\add* said,
\pi1
\v 4 Yisrael's godВҰ317519, Commander-in-chief YahwehВҰ317517 saysВҰ317516 this to all \add вүҲof you\add* that I've exiledВҰ317523 from YerushalemВҰ317527 to BabylonВҰ317528:
\v 5 BuildВҰ317530 housesВҰ317531 and live in them, and plantВҰ317533 gardensВҰ317534 and eatВҰ317535 theirВҰ317538 fruit.
\v 6 \add вүҲMarry\add* and \add вүҲhave children\add*. \add вүҲFind\add* wives for your sons and give your daughters \add вүҲin marriage\add* so that they \add also\add* \add вүҲhave children\add*. \add вүҲIncrease in number\add* thereВҰ317558вҖ”don'tВҰ317559 become fewer.
\v 7 \add вүҲIn additionВҰ317563, the cityВҰ317567 that I'veВҰ317569 sentВҰ317569 you all into exileВҰ317569 to, work to make it more prosperous\add* andВҰ317563 pray to YahwehВҰ317576 for it, becauseВҰ317577 \add вүҲif it prospers, its prosperity will belongВҰ317579 to all of you\add*.
\v 8 That's becauseВҰ317584 Yisrael's godВҰ317589, Commander-in-chief YahwehВҰ317587 saysВҰ317586 this: Don'tВҰ317591 let your prophetsВҰ317595 and divinersВҰ317599 who are among you deceiveВҰ317593 you, and don'tВҰ317591 listenВҰ317602 to your dreamsВҰ317605 thatВҰ317606 you \add wishfully\add* dream,
\v 9 because \add @those prophets\add* are prophesyingВҰ317613 \add вүҲusing\add* my nameВҰ317615 \add вүҲbut not being truthful\add*вҖ”I didn'tВҰ317616 send them. That is Yahweh'sВҰ317620 declaration.
\p
\v 10 вҖңBecause this is what YahwehВҰ317627 saysВҰ317626: When seventyВҰ317632 years \add вүҲhave passed\add* for BabylonВҰ317631, I'll visit \add вүҲtake notice of you all\add* \add again\add*, andВҰ317636 I'll \add вүҲimplement\add* my goodВҰ317641 messageВҰ317640 about youвҖ”to bringВҰ317642 you all back to this placeВҰ317646,\x + \xo 29:10: \xt 2Ch 36:21; Jer 25:11; Dan 9:2.\x*
\v 11 because I knowВҰ317651 the plans thatВҰ317655 I \add вүҲhave\add* for you all: plans for peaceful well-beingвҖ”not to bring you all harm, \add butВҰ317664 rather\add* a futureВҰ317668 \add вүҲwith\add* hope. That is Yahweh'sВҰ317661 declaration.
\v 12 ThenВҰ317671 you'll all callВҰ317671 out to me \add for help\add*, and you'll comeВҰ317673 and pray to me, and I'llВҰ317676 listenВҰ317676 to you all.
\v 13 You'll searchВҰ317679 for me, andВҰ317681 you'll find me, becauseВҰ317682 you'll all \add вүҲwant to follow me with complete sincerity\add*.\x + \xo 29:13: \xt Deu 4:29.\x*
\v 14 ThenВҰ317688, Yahweh has declared, I'll let myselfВҰ317688 be foundВҰ317688 by you all, and I'll \add вүҲbring you back from\add* captivityВҰ317696. I'll gatherВҰ317698 you all from all the nationsВҰ317702 and all the placesВҰ317705 that I banishedВҰ317707 you to, and I'll bring you all back to the placeВҰ317717 that I sent you into exileВҰ317720 from. That is Yahweh'sВҰ317692 declaration.
\pi1
\v 15 Because you've all saidВҰ317725 that YahwehВҰ317728 has \add вүҲappointed\add* prophetsВҰ317729 for \add %you\add* \add there\add* in BabylonВҰ317730,
\v 16 \add вүҲthen\add* YahwehВҰ317738 \add вүҲhas something to say\add* about the kingВҰ317741 sitting on David'sВҰ317746 throneВҰ317745 andВҰ317747 about all the peopleВҰ317751 living in this cityВҰ317753вҖ”your relatives who didn'tВҰ317757 go into exileВҰ317761 with you.
\v 17 So Commander-in-chief YahwehВҰ317765 saysВҰ317764: Listen, I'm aboutВҰ317768 to sendВҰ317768 \add вүҲwar\add*, famineВҰ317775 and \add вүҲdeadly diseases\add* against them. I'llВҰ317779 makeВҰ317779 them like rottenВҰ317782 figsВҰ317781 thatВҰ317783 are so bad they're \add вүҲinedible\add*.
\v 18 \add вүҲYes,\add* I'll chase afterВҰ317790 them with \add вүҲwar\add*, famineВҰ317792, and \add вүҲdeadly diseases\add*, and I'll makeВҰ317794 them become a horror to all the \add вүҲworld's\add* kingdomsВҰ317799вҖ”a curseВҰ317801 and a desolation, and a reproachВҰ317804 and \add вүҲsomething to be hissed at\add* by all the nationsВҰ317807 whereВҰ317808 I'veВҰ317810 driven them,
\v 19 because theyВҰ317818 didn't listen to my messages thatВҰ317825 I sentВҰ317826 to them \add вүҲover and over again\add* via my servantsВҰ317830 the prophetsВҰ317831, butВҰ317833 all you \add exiles\add* didn't listen. That is Yahweh'sВҰ317824 declaration.
\p
\v 20 \add вүҲButВҰ317840\add* all you exilesВҰ317847 that I sentВҰ317850 away from YerushalemВҰ317851 to BabylonВҰ317852, listenВҰ317841 to Yahweh'sВҰ317844 messageВҰ317842:
\pi1
\v 21 Yisrael's godВҰ317860, Commander-in-chief YahwehВҰ317858, saysВҰ317857 this aboutВҰ317880 Kolayah'sВҰ317867 son Ahav and Maaseyah'sВҰ317873 son Tsidkiyah, who are \add both\add* prophesyingВҰ317874 untruths to you in my nameВҰ317876: Listen, I'm \add вүҲhanding them over\add* to the Babylonian KingВҰ317884 NebuchadnezzarВҰ317883, and he'll \add вүҲkill them right in front of you\add*.
\v 22 ThenВҰ317890 because of them, a \add new\add* curseВҰ317892 \add phrase\add* will be takenВҰ317890 on by all the \add вүҲJewish\add* exilesВҰ317894 in BabylonВҰ317897, which goes, вҖңMay YahwehВҰ317900 makeВҰ317899 youВҰ317899 like Tsidkiyah andВҰ317902 Ahav, who were roastedВҰ317905 in the fireВҰ317909 by the Babylonian kingВҰ317906,вҖқ
\v 23 because they didВҰ317913 something shameful in YisraelВҰ317915 and they have committedВҰ317916 adulteryВҰ317916 with the wivesВҰ317919 of their neighboursВҰ317920, and they spokeВҰ317921 untrue messagesВҰ317922 in my nameВҰ317923 that I hadn't commandedВҰ317927 them to. I am the one \add вүҲwho knows that\add* and I'm a witnessВҰ317933. That is Yahweh'sВҰ317936 declaration.
\s1 Message to false prophet Shemayah
\rem /s1 A Message for Shemaiah; Message to Shemaiah; The Letter of Shemaiah
\p
\v 24 \add Yahweh told me to\add* tell ShemayahВҰ317941 (the NehelamiteВҰ317942) this:
\v 25 Yisrael's godВҰ317951, Commander-in-chief YahwehВҰ317949 saysВҰ317948 this: Because you sentВҰ317957 lettersВҰ317959 in your nameВҰ317958 to all the peopleВҰ317964 in YerushalemВҰ317966, and to the priestВҰ317973 Tsefanyah (Maaseyah'sВҰ317972 son), and to all the priestsВҰ317977, to tell \add <Tsefanyah\add*:
\pi1
\v 26 Yahweh has made you, \add Tsefanyah,\add* priest in placeВҰ317983 of the priest Yehoyada \add (Jehoiada)\add*, to be \add #overseer\add* in Yahweh'sВҰ317980 \add вүҲtemple\add* over every man who raves \add out loud\add*, making himself a prophetВҰ317994, and you mustВҰ317995 put him in the stocksВҰ317999 \add вүҲwith an iron collarВҰ318002 around his\add* neck.
\v 27 \add вүҲSoВҰ318004 why\add* haven't you rebukedВҰ318007 Yirmeyah the Antotite who's prophesyingВҰ318010 to you all,
\v 28 because he's sentВҰ318017 \add a letter\add* to us \add here\add* in BabylonВҰ318019 saying, вҖң\add @Your exile\add* \add вүҲwill last a longВҰ318021 time\add*. Build housesВҰ318024 and live in them. Plant gardensВҰ318027 and eatВҰ318028 theirВҰ318031 fruit.вҖқ
\p
\v 29 The priestВҰ318035 Tsefanyah read that letterВҰ318038 to the prophetВҰ318042 Yirmeyah,
\v 30 then YahwehВҰ318048 \add вүҲgave\add* this messageВҰ318046 to YirmeyahВҰ318051:
\v 31 Send to all the \add #exiles\add* to tell them: This is what YahwehВҰ318063 saysВҰ318062 about Shemayah the NehelamiteВҰ318067: Because Shemayah has prophesiedВҰ318070 to you all, \add вүҲeven though\add* I didn'tВҰ318074 send him, and he madeВҰ318076 you trust \add вүҲwhat's not true\add*,
\v 32 therefore Yahweh says this: Listen, I \add вүҲwill punish\add* ShemayahВҰ318091 the NehelamiteВҰ318092 and \add вүҲhis descendants\add*. \add вүҲNone of his family\add* will live among this people, and \add вүҲhe won'tВҰ318096 experience the good things\add* thatВҰ318112 I'llВҰ318114 do for my people, becauseВҰ318121 he's \add вүҲencouraged\add* rebellionВҰ318123 against Yahweh. That is Yahweh'sВҰ318086 declaration.
