\v 35 Yahweh says this:
\q1 \add I'm\add* the one who givesВҰ319196 the sun for light during the dayВҰ319199,
\q1 вүҲand the moon and the starsВҰ319202 for light at nightВҰ319204.
\q1 He stirsВҰ319205 up the ocean, so that its wavesВҰ319208 roar,
\q1 His name is Commander-in-chief Yahweh.
\q1
\v 36 YahwehВҰ319221 declares that if theseВҰ319217 \add вүҲelements\add* stopped working,
\q1 then YisraelВҰ319224 would also permanently ceaseВҰ319225 to exist as a nationВҰ319227.
\p
\v 37 YahwehВҰ319237 saysВҰ319236 this:
\q1 If the skiesВҰ319241 aboveВҰ319242 could be measuredВҰ319240 andВҰ319243 be searched out,
\q1 as well as the foundationsВҰ319244 of the earthВҰ319246 below,
\q1 then I would also rejectВҰ319251 all of Yisrael's descendants
\q2 for everything that they've doneВҰ319261.
\m That is Yahweh'sВҰ319237 declaration.
\rem /s1 Jerusalem to Be Enlarged
\p
\v 38 Listen, Yahweh declares that \add вүҲthe timeВҰ319268\add* is coming when the cityВҰ319275 will be \add re\add*rebuilt for YahwehвҖ”from Hananel'sВҰ319278 towerВҰ319277 \add all the way\add* to the Corner Gate.
\v 39 \add вүҲAfter that,\add* the measuringВҰ319284 line will \add вүҲbe stretched\add* over Garev Hill andВҰ319291 \add вүҲaround\add* to GoahВҰ319292.
\v 40 ThenВҰ319294 all the valleyВҰ319296 of the corpsesВҰ319297 and ashes, and all the fieldsВҰ319302 as far as the KidronВҰ319307 brook, to the cornerВҰ319310 of the Horses Gate toward the east, will be holiness to YahwehВҰ319315. It won'tВҰ319316 be uprooted, and it'll never be overthrown againВҰ319322.
\c 32
\s1 Yirmeyah buys a field
\rem /s1 Jeremiah Buys a Field During the Siege; Jeremiah's Land Purchase; Jeremiah Buys a Field
\p
\v 1 This was the messageВҰ319326 thatВҰ319327 came to Yirmeyah from YahwehВҰ319334 in the tenthВҰ319337 year of \add the reign of\add* Yehudah'sВҰ319340 KingВҰ319339 Tsidkiyah \add (ZedekiahВҰ319338\add*, the eighteenthВҰ319343 year of Nebuchadnezzar'sВҰ319347 \add reign)\add*.\x + \xo 32:1: \xt 2Ki 25:1-7.\x*
\v 2 The army of the Babylonian king had besieged YerushalemВҰ319356, andВҰ319349 the prophetВҰ319358 Yirmeyah was imprisoned in the guards' courtyardВҰ319361 at the \add вүҲpalace\add* of Yehudah'sВҰ319367 king.
\v 3 Yehudah'sВҰ319374 king Tsidkiyah had imprisoned him \add there after asking\add*, вҖңWhy do you prophesyВҰ319378 and say that YahwehВҰ319382 says: Listen, I'm aboutВҰ319384 to \add вүҲhandВҰ319389\add* this cityВҰ319387 over to the Babylonian king and he'll captureВҰ319393 it.
\v 4 Yehudah'sВҰ319397 KingВҰ319396 Tsidkiyah definitely won'tВҰ319398 escapeВҰ319399 from the \add вүҲpower\add* of the \add вүҲBabylonians\add* \add (Heb. Chaldeans)\add*, becauseВҰ319402 he'll be \add вүҲhanded over\add* to the Babylonian king andВҰ319395 \add вүҲthey'll speakВҰ319409 face-to-face to each other\add*.
\v 5 He'll takeВҰ319423 Tsidkiyah to Babylon \add вүҲwhere\add* he'll remain untilВҰ319429 \add вүҲI've dealt\add* with him. \add вүҲNo,\add* you all won'tВҰ319441 succeedВҰ319442 in fightingВҰ319437 against the \add вүҲBabylonians\add*. That is Yahweh'sВҰ319435 declaration.
\p
\v 6 Then Yirmeyah saidВҰ319445: YahwehВҰ319450 \add вүҲgave\add* me a messageВҰ319448, saying:
\v 7 Listen, your \add cousin\add* HanamelВҰ319455 (your uncleВҰ319459 Shallum'sВҰ319458 son) is coming to \add see\add* you and will \add вүҲask\add* you to buy \add %his\add* fieldВҰ319467 in AnatotВҰ319469, becauseВҰ319470 you have the rightВҰ319472 to buy it.
\v 8 Then just as Yahweh \add вүҲhad said\add*, my \add вүҲcousin\add* HanamelВҰ319478 came to me in the guards' courtyardВҰ319486 andВҰ319476 he \add вүҲasked\add* me, вҖңBuy my fieldВҰ319494 that is in AnatotВҰ319497 in the BenyaminВҰ319501 \add вүҲregionВҰ319500\add*, becauseВҰ319502 you have the right to inherit it \add вүҲso\add* the right to buy it belongsВҰ319507 to you. Buy it for yourselfВҰ319504.вҖқ Then I knew that this was Yahweh'sВҰ319483 message.
\v 9 \add вүҲSoВҰ319519\add* I boughtВҰ319519 the fieldВҰ319522 in AnatotВҰ319529 from my \add вүҲcousin\add* HanamelВҰ319524, andВҰ319519 I weighedВҰ319530 out seventeenВҰ319536 shekelsВҰ319537 of silver for him.
\v 10 ThenВҰ319541 I wroteВҰ319541 in a scroll and sealedВҰ319543 it, and had witnesses witness it \add вүҲand the weightВҰ319546 of\add* the silverВҰ319547 on the scales.
\v 11 Next I tookВҰ319550 \add &that\add* sealedВҰ319557 purchaseВҰ319554 \add вүҲdeed\add* with the \add вүҲprice\add* andВҰ319550 conditionsВҰ319559, \add вүҲas well as an unsealed copy\add*.
\v 12 I gaveВҰ319564 the \add sealed\add* purchase document to Baruk (son of Neriyah, son of MahseyahВҰ319577) \add вүҲin front of\add* my \add вүҲcousin\add* HanamelВҰ319579 andВҰ319564 the witnessesВҰ319582 who'd \add вүҲsigned\add* the purchase agreement, as well as all the Judeans who were sittingВҰ319590 in the guards' courtyardВҰ319591.
\v 13 ThenВҰ319594 \add still\add* \add вүҲin front of them\add*, I \add вүҲinstructedВҰ319594\add* Baruk,
\v 14 Yisrael's godВҰ319606, Commander-in-chief YahwehВҰ319604 saysВҰ319603 this: Take theseВҰ319612 documentsВҰ319611, both this receipt of purchaseВҰ319615 that's sealedВҰ319618 and the unsealed copies, and put them into a clay jar so they'll last for a long timeВҰ319629,
\v 15 becauseВҰ319633 Yisrael's godВҰ319638, Commander-in-chief YahwehВҰ319636 saysВҰ319635 this: Houses, fieldsВҰ319643, and vineyardsВҰ319644 will againВҰ319640 be boughtВҰ319641 in this land.
\s1 Yirmeyah's prayer
\rem /s1 Jeremiah's Prayer; Jeremiah Prays for Understanding
\p
\v 16 After I'd given the purchaseВҰ319658 \add вүҲdeed\add* to Neriyah's son Baruk, I prayedВҰ319649 to YahwehВҰ319652, saying:
\v 17 Oh no, masterВҰ319668 YahwehВҰ319668. Listen, you alone madeВҰ319673 the heavensВҰ319676 and the earthВҰ319679 \add вүҲby taking action\add* and using your incredible strengthВҰ319680. Nothing you say is too difficultВҰ319686 for you to do.
\v 18 You show loyalВҰ319693 commitment to thousandsВҰ319694, and pour people's guilt into their children'sВҰ319701 \add вүҲlaps\add* afterВҰ319702 them. You are the strong and powerful godВҰ319703вҖ”your nameВҰ319708 is Commander-in-chief YahwehВҰ319706.
\v 19 You are \add вүҲvery wise\add* and \add вүҲdo incredible things\add*, because your eyesВҰ319716 are open to all the people's waysвҖ”to give each person what their conduct and actions deserve.
\v 20 You did \add вүҲmiracles and amazing things\add* in EgyptВҰ319738 \add (Heb. Mitsrayim)\add*, \add ?remembered\add* to this day, and you'veВҰ319745 made a name for yourselfВҰ319747 in YisraelВҰ319743 and amongВҰ319744 humankindВҰ319744.
\v 21 You broughtВҰ319752 your peopleВҰ319755 YisraelВҰ319758 out from EgyptВҰ319760 using \add вүҲmiracles and amazing things\add* and \add вүҲby taking action\add* and using your incredible strength, along with greatВҰ319768 terrorВҰ319767.
\v 22 ThenВҰ319770 you gave them this land whichВҰ319776 you had promisedВҰ319778 theirВҰ319779 ancestorsВҰ319779 thatВҰ319776 you'd give themвҖ”a land flowingВҰ319783 with milk andВҰ319770 honeyВҰ319785.
\v 23 \add вүҲSoВҰ319787\add* they entered andВҰ319787 tookВҰ319788 possessionВҰ319788 of it, \add вүҲbutВҰ319787\add* they didn't listenВҰ319792 to your voiceВҰ319793 or follow your instructionsВҰ319803. They didn't do anything that you'd orderedВҰ319803 them to do \add вүҲso\add* you'veВҰ319808 brought all this calamityВҰ319813 onto them.
\p
\v 24 Look, the siege moundsВҰ319817 have \add вүҲreached up\add* to the city to captureВҰ319820 it, and its been \add вүҲhanded over\add* to the Babylonians \add (Heb. Chaldeans)\add* who've been fightingВҰ319825 it. Everything you said would happenВҰ319833 has, includingВҰ319821 \add вүҲwar\add*, famineВҰ319829, and deadly diseases, and you'reВҰ319834 thereВҰ319834 watching it.
\v 25 ThenВҰ319837 you yourself told me, вҖҳUse silverВҰ319846 to buy yourself a fieldВҰ319845, andВҰ319837 have witnesses witness it, even though this cityВҰ319849 is being \add вүҲhanded over to the Babylonians\add* \add (Heb. Chaldeans)\add*.вҖҷ
\rem /s1 God's Assurance of the People's Return; A Prediction of Jerusalem's Fall
\p
\v 26 ThenВҰ319854 YahwehВҰ319857 \add вүҲgave\add* YirmeyahВҰ319860 \add &this\add* messageВҰ319855:
\v 27 Listen, I'm YahwehВҰ319865, the godВҰ319866 of all \add вүҲmankind\add*. Is there anything that's too difficultВҰ319871 for me to do?
\v 28 Therefore YahwehВҰ319879 says this, вҖҳListen, I'm aboutВҰ319881 to \add вүҲhand\add* this cityВҰ319884 over to the \add вүҲBabylonians\add*вҖ”the Babylonian KingВҰ319890 NebuchadnezzarВҰ319889 will captureВҰ319893 it.\x + \xo 32:28: \xt 2Ki 25:1-11; 2Ch 36:17-21.\x*
\v 29 The \add вүҲsoldiers\add* who are fightingВҰ319897 against this city will come and set fire to this city and burn it. Those peopleВҰ319912 who worship BaalВҰ319916 on their \add flat\add* roofsВҰ319915, and who pouredВҰ319917 out drinkВҰ319918 offeringsВҰ319918 to otherВҰ319920 gods in order to provokeВҰ319922 me, will \add now\add* have their housesВҰ319910 burnt down
\v 30 becauseВҰ319937 the people of YisraelВҰ319929 and YehudahВҰ319931 have certainly been people who've been doingВҰ319933 evil \add вүҲin front of me\add* sinceВҰ319936 their youthВҰ319936. The people of IsraelВҰ319929 have certainly offended me with the practices \add вүҲand activities\add*. That is Yahweh'sВҰ319948 declaration.
\v 31 Yahweh declares that \add the people of\add* this cityВҰ319959 has \add вүҲprovoked\add* my angerВҰ319953 and fury since the day that they builtВҰ319965 it, and then right up to the present day, \add вүҲso\add* I'll will removeВҰ319970 it \add right\add* \add вүҲout of my sight\add*,
\v 32 \add вүҲbecause of\add* all the wicked things thatВҰ319983 the peopleВҰ319978 of YisraelВҰ319980 and Yehudah have doneВҰ319984 to provokeВҰ319985 meвҖ”their kingsВҰ319987, princes, priestsВҰ319989, prophetsВҰ319990, and everyВҰ319991 person in Yehudah \add вүҲincludingВҰ319981\add* Yerushalem'sВҰ319994 inhabitantsВҰ319993.
\v 33 They turnedВҰ319996 their backs to me instead of their faces, even though I had \add вүҲeagerly\add* taughtВҰ320001 them. I tried to teachВҰ320004 them, butВҰ319996 they wouldn't listenВҰ320006 \add вүҲor\add* receive correctionВҰ320008.
\v 34 They set up theirВҰ320011 detestableВҰ320011 \add >idols\add* in the houseВҰ320012 thatВҰ320013 is calledВҰ320015 by my nameВҰ320017, \add in order\add* to defile it,\x + \xo 32:34: \xt 2Ki 23:10; Jer 7:30-31; 19:1-6.\x*
\v 35 and they builtВҰ320021 \add вүҲhilltopВҰ320024 shrinesВҰ320024\add* for BaalВҰ320025 along the Ben-Hinnom ValleyВҰ320031 in order to passВҰ320032 their sonsВҰ320035 and daughtersВҰ320038 throughВҰ320032 the fire for MolekВҰ320039.\x + \xo 32:35: \xt 2Ki 23:10; Jer 7:31.\x* I didn'tВҰ320041 commandВҰ320043 them \add to do that\add*вҖ”itВҰ320045 never entered my mindВҰ320048 that they should do that detestable thing and so causeВҰ320053 YehudahВҰ320057 to sinВҰ320053.вҖҷ\x + \xo 32:35: \xt Lev 18:21.\x*
\s1 Promised restoration
\rem /s1 A Promise of Hope; A Promise of Restoration
\p
\v 36 So now Yisrael's godВҰ320066 YahwehВҰ320065 \add вүҲhas something to say\add* about this cityВҰ320070 thatВҰ320072 you've all been talkingВҰ320075 about, sayingВҰ320075, вҖҳIt's \add вүҲbeen handed over\add* to the Babylonian kingВҰ320078 \add due to\add* \add вүҲwar\add*, famineВҰ320082, and \add вүҲdeadly diseases\add*.вҖҷ
\v 37 Listen, I'llВҰ320085 gatherВҰ320086 them \add back\add* from every land whereВҰ320090 I had banishedВҰ320091 them to in my rage, fury, and greatВҰ320096 anger. I'm about to bringВҰ320097 them back to this placeВҰ320100 and enable them to live in securityВҰ320103,
\v 38 and thenВҰ320105 they'll be my peopleВҰ320107 and I'llВҰ320109 be their godВҰ320111.
\v 39 I'llВҰ320113 giveВҰ320113 them \add вүҲa united vision\add* and a single wayВҰ320117 to honour me every day so that it'll \add turn out\add* goodВҰ320124 for them and for theirВҰ320126 descendants afterВҰ320127 them.
\v 40 ThenВҰ320129 I'll makeВҰ320129 a permanentВҰ320132 agreementВҰ320131 with them, that I won'tВҰ320134 turn away from doing good to them. I'll set honour for me in theirВҰ320144 \add вүҲminds\add*, so that they'll never turn away from me.
\v 41 ThenВҰ320149 I'll \add вүҲtake pleasure\add* in doing goodВҰ320151 to them. I'll faithfullyВҰ320156 plantВҰ320153 them in this land with all my heartВҰ320159 andВҰ320149 all my life
\v 42 becauseВҰ320165 YahwehВҰ320169 saysВҰ320168 this, вҖҳJust as I have broughtВҰ320171 all this greatВҰ320180 disaster on this peopleВҰ320174, so too I'llВҰ320183 bringВҰ320184 on them all the goodВҰ320190 things thatВҰ320191 I'veВҰ320171 said I'd do for them.
\v 43 ThenВҰ320196 \add people\add* will buy fieldsВҰ320197 in this land, about whichВҰ320200 you've been sayingВҰ320203, вҖңThis land is ruined, without people or \add even\add* animalsВҰ320208 \add living\add* on it. It's been \add вүҲhanded over to\add* the \add вүҲBabylonians\add*.вҖқ
\v 44 They'll use silverВҰ320214 to buy fieldsВҰ320213 and will writeВҰ320216 in sealed scrolls. They'll assemble witnessesВҰ320220 in the BenyaminВҰ320223 \add вүҲregionВҰ320222\add*, all around YerushalemВҰ320225 and Yehudah'sВҰ320227 \add other\add* cities of Judah, in the cities in the hill countryВҰ320229 and in the lowlands, and in the cities of the NegevВҰ320233, becauseВҰ320234 I'llВҰ320236 \add вүҲbring back theirВҰ320239 fortunes\add*. That is Yahweh'sВҰ320242 declaration.
\c 33
\s1 Promised blessings
\rem /s1 Promises of Peace and Prosperity; Another Promise of Hope; Healing after Punishment; Promise of Restoration
\p
\v 1 вҮ”Then while YirmeyahВҰ320251 was stillВҰ320254 locked in the guards' courtyardВҰ320256, YahwehВҰ320248 \add вүҲgave\add* him a secondВҰ320252 messageВҰ320246, saying,
\v 2 Yahweh, the maker \add of the earth\add*, who formedВҰ320266 \add вүҲand establishedВҰ320268 it\add* and \add who's known by\add* his nameВҰ320270 Yahweh, saysВҰ320262:
\v 3 Call \add out\add* to me, and I'll answerВҰ320274 you. I'll tell you \add вүҲamazing\add* \add >things\add* thatВҰ320279 you haven't \add previously\add* known \add вүҲor understood\add*.
\v 4 \add вүҲYes,\add* Yisrael's godВҰ320287, YahwehВҰ320286, says this about the houses in this cityВҰ320292 and the \add вүҲpalaces\add* of Yehudah'sВҰ320298 king thatВҰ320299 were torn down \add to be used against\add* the siege ramps and the \add вүҲattackers\add*:
\v 5 The \add вүҲBabylonians\add* are comingВҰ320307 to fightВҰ320308, and to fillВҰ320312 the houses with the corpsesВҰ320315 of the people thatВҰ320317 I'll kill in my rageВҰ320321 and fury when I \add вүҲturn my back on\add* this cityВҰ320325 because of all theirВҰ320330 wickedness.
\v 6 Listen, I'm about to bring a cure and healing, because I'llВҰ320332 heal them and will bring bountiful peace and prosperity to them, and \add ?вүҲjustice\add*.
\v 7 I'll \add вүҲbring back the fortunes\add* of YehudahВҰ320349 andВҰ320345 YisraelВҰ320352вҖ”I'll build them up as \add вүҲthey were before\add*.
\v 8 ThenВҰ320356 I'll purify them from all the \add вүҲevil\add* that they've committed against meвҖ”I'll pardon all the \add вүҲtimes that they disobeyed\add* me, andВҰ320356 all the ways that they rebelledВҰ320374 against me.
\v 9 Then this city will becomeВҰ320377 \add an object\add* of joyВҰ320380 for meвҖ”a song of praiseВҰ320381 and honourВҰ320382 for all the nationsВҰ320384 of the earthВҰ320385 who'll hearВҰ320387 about all the good things that I'm going to do for it. Then \add @the people in the city\add* will \add вүҲbe respectful\add* and trembleВҰ320398 because of all the good things and the peace and prosperity that I'llВҰ320394 give to it.
\p
\v 10 YahwehВҰ320416 says this: In this place that you're all talkingВҰ320424 about, sayingВҰ320424, вҖңIt's desolateвҖ”a place where neither people or animals \add live\add*,вҖқ in Yehudah'sВҰ320432 citiesВҰ320431 \add вүҲincludingВҰ320429\add* Yerushalem'sВҰ320434 streetsВҰ320433 that are \add indeed\add* desolate \add вүҲwith no people or animals around\add*, there'll be heardВҰ320418 againВҰ320417
\v 11 the sounds of happiness and \add вүҲcelebration\add*. \add вүЎYou'll all hear\add* the sounds of the brideВҰ320448 and groom, and thoseВҰ320452 who bringВҰ320466 thank offerings to Yahweh'sВҰ320456 \add вүҲtemple\add* will be heard saying,
\q1 вҖңGive thanks to Commander-in-chief Yahweh,
\q1 becauseВҰ320458 Yahweh is goodВҰ320460,
\q1 and his loyalВҰ320465 commitment lasts foreverВҰ320464!вҖқ
\m \add вүҲYes,\add* I'llВҰ320472 \add вүҲrestore the fortunes of\add* the land to what they were before, saysВҰ320479 Yahweh.\x + \xo 33:11: \xt 1Ch 16:34; 2Ch 5:13; 7:3; Ezr 3:11; Psa 100:5; 106:1; 107:1; 118:1; 136:1.\x*
\p
\v 12 Commander-in-chief YahwehВҰ320486 saysВҰ320485: вҖҳIn this desolateВҰ320493 placeВҰ320491 where \add вүҲno people or animalsВҰ320499\add* \add are living\add*, around all itsВҰ320502 citiesВҰ320502 there'll againВҰ320488 be pasturesВҰ320503 where shepherdsВҰ320504 \add вүҲcan rest\add* their flocksВҰ320506.
\v 13 InВҰ320511 the cities in the hill country, the lowlands, and the NegevВҰ320513, in the BenyaminВҰ320515 \add regionВҰ320514\add*, and all around YerushalemВҰ320517 and in Yehudah'sВҰ320519 \add other\add* cities, the flocksВҰ320522 will againВҰ320520 pass \add вүҲbe counted by their shepherds\add*,вҖҷ says YahwehВҰ320528.
\rem /s1 The Righteous Branch and the Covenant with David
\p
\v 14 YahwehВҰ320536 declares: ListenВҰ320531, \add вүҲthe timeВҰ320532\add* is comingВҰ320533 when I'llВҰ320537 do what I'veВҰ320543 promised for the \add вүҲpeople\add* of YisraelВҰ320547 and YehudahВҰ320551.
\v 15 In thoseВҰ320554 daysВҰ320553 and at that timeВҰ320555, I'llВҰ320557 make a \add вүҲrighteous\add* branchВҰ320559 grow for DavidВҰ320558, and he'll \add вүҲdoВҰ320561 what's fair and right throughout\add* the land.
\v 16 YehudahВҰ320569 will be rescued in thoseВҰ320567 daysВҰ320566, and YerushalemВҰ320570 will live in securityВҰ320572, because it'll be called, вҖҳYahwehВҰ320579 is \add вүҲthe one who does what's rightВҰ320581 for us\add*,вҖҷ
\v 17 becauseВҰ320584 YahwehВҰ320588 saysВҰ320587 this: вҖҳ\add вүҲThere'll always be one of David'sВҰ320592 descendants reigning over\add* YisraelВҰ320600,\x + \xo 33:17: \xt 2Sam 7:12-16; 1Ki 2:4; 1Ch 17:11-14.\x*
\v 18 and \add вүҲthere'll always be a LeviticalВҰ320603 priestВҰ320602 to stand in frontВҰ320608 of\add* me to sacrifice burntВҰ320610 offerings, to burn grainВҰ320612 offerings, and to offer other sacrifices.вҖҷ\x + \xo 33:18: \xt Num 3:5-10.\x*
\p
\v 19 Then YahwehВҰ320625 \add вүҲgave\add* Yirmeyah \add &this\add* messageВҰ320623:
\v 20 YahwehВҰ320633 says this: вҖҳIf you all can breakВҰ320636 my contract with day and night so that there'll no longer be day or night at theirВҰ320650 proper times,
\v 21 then my agreement with my servant DavidВҰ320658 my servant could \add also\add* be brokenВҰ320655, so that he would no longer have a descendant to sit on his throneВҰ320667. \add вүЎThe same is true for\add* my agreement with my servantsВҰ320672, the priestsВҰ320671 \add вүҲfrom LeviВҰ320670 tribe\add*.
\v 22 As the stars in the skiesВҰ320679 can't be countedВҰ320677, and as the sand \add grains\add* on the seashores can't be measuredВҰ320681, so I'llВҰ320685 increaseВҰ320685 the descendants of myВҰ320694 servantВҰ320690 DavidВҰ320689, as well as the LevitesВҰ320693 who \add вүҲwork for\add* me.вҖҷ
\p
\v 23 YahwehВҰ320701 \add вүҲgave\add* YirmeyahВҰ320704 \add &this\add* messageВҰ320699:
\v 24 Haven't you \add вүҲnoticed\add* what this people \add group\add* has declared when they said, вҖҳThe two clansВҰ320716 that YahwehВҰ320719 choseВҰ320718, now he's rejectedВҰ320721 themвҖҷ? In that way they despise my people, saying that they no longer \add вүҲdeserve to be\add* a nationВҰ320728 \add вүҲas far as they're concerned\add*.
\v 25 \add ButВҰ320740\add* \add вүҲI,\add* YahwehВҰ320734 say this: Didn't I establish the \add permanent\add* contract with day and nightВҰ320740, and determine the laws of \add вүҲthe universe\add* and \add вүҲthis planet\add*?
\v 26 \add вүҲIn the same way,\add* would I \add now\add* rejectВҰ320754 Yakov's descendants and not bring a rulerВҰ320757 for the descendants of AbrahamВҰ320761, Yitshak, and Yakov out of them. \add No,\add* becauseВҰ320764 I'llВҰ320754 \add вүҲrestore theirВҰ320770 fortunes\add* and \add вүҲshow mercy towards\add* them.
\c 34
\s1 The warning for Tsidkiyah/Zedekiah
\rem /s1 Death in Captivity Predicted for Zedekiah; Events under Jehoiakim and Zedekiah; A Warning for Zedekiah; Warning to Zedekiah; A Message for Zedekiah
\p
\v 1 YahwehВҰ320782 \add вүҲgave\add* this messageВҰ320774 to Yirmeyah when the Babylonian KingВҰ320784 NebuchadnezzarВҰ320783, along with all the \add вүҲworld's\add* kingdomsВҰ320793, domains, and peopleВҰ320799 \add groups\add* under his \add вүҲcontrol\add*, was \add вүҲattacking\add* YerushalemВҰ320803 and \add вүҲYehudah's other\add* citiesВҰ320808, saying:\x + \xo 34:1: \xt 2Ki 25:1-11; 2Ch 36:17-21.\x*
\v 2 Yisrael's godВҰ320815 Yahweh says to go and speak to Yehudah'sВҰ320823 KingВҰ320822 Tsidkiyah \add (ZedekiahВҰ320821)\add* and tell him that Yahweh says this: Listen, I'm aboutВҰ320830 to \add вүҲhandВҰ320835 this cityВҰ320833 over\add* to the Babylonian king, and he'll \add вүҲset it on fireВҰ320840\add*.
\v 3 You won'tВҰ320843 escapeВҰ320844 from his \add вүҲpower\add*, becauseВҰ320846 you'll definitely be capturedВҰ320847 and \add вүҲhanded over to him\add* and you'll \add вүҲtalk face-to-face with\add* the kingВҰ320855 of Babylon as you're \add вүҲtaken\add* to Babylon.
\v 4 However KingВҰ320873 Tsidkiyah, listenВҰ320868 to Yahweh'sВҰ320871 messageВҰ320869вҖ”you won'tВҰ320880 be \add вүҲkilled by being run through with a\add* swordВҰ320882
\v 5 \add butВҰ320886 actually\add* you'll dieВҰ320885 in peaceВҰ320884. They'll \add вүҲcremate\add* your body as was done for your ancestorsВҰ320887, the previous kingsВҰ320888, and they'll mournВҰ320900 for you \add saying,\add*, вҖҳOh no, masterВҰ320899!вҖҷ That's the promiseВҰ320905 that YahwehВҰ320899 has declared.
\v 6 \add вүҲSo\add* the prophetВҰ320916 Yirmeyah \add вүҲpassed on\add* all those messages to Yehudah'sВҰ320921 KingВҰ320920 Tsidkiyah in YerushalemВҰ320927
\v 7 \add вүҲwhen\add* the Babylonian king's army had attacked YerushalemВҰ320936 and Yehudah'sВҰ320941 remainingВҰ320951 fortifiedВҰ320955 cities of Lakish and AzekahВҰ320948.
\s1 The restoration of slaves
\rem /s1 Treacherous Treatment of Slaves; Deceitful Treatment of Slaves; Freedom for Slaves; Freedom for Hebrew Slaves
\p
\v 8 YahwehВҰ320966 \add вүҲgave\add* a messageВҰ320958 to Yirmeyah afterВҰ320967 KingВҰ320969 Tsidkiyah had madeВҰ320968 an agreementВҰ320971 with all the peopleВҰ320976 in YerushalemВҰ320978 thatВҰ320959 \add вүҲthey'd free\add*
\v 9 their male and femaleВҰ320991 Hebrew slavesвҖ”\add вүҲno one shouldВҰ320983 force a fellow Jew\add* to workВҰ320996 for them.
\v 10 \add вүҲSoВҰ321003\add* all the leaders and peopleВҰ321009 \add вүҲformally agreed\add* that each person would free their male and femaleВҰ321022 slaves, and they \add вүҲput it into practiceвҖ”taking them from their workВҰ321025\add* and setting them free.
\v 11 \add вүҲHowever,\add* afterВҰ321033 that they \add вүҲchanged their minds\add* and \add вүҲretrieved\add* the male and female slaves that they'd freed, thenВҰ321032 forcedВҰ321046 them to \add вүҲwork as slaves again\add*.
\p
\v 12 Then YahwehВҰ321055 \add вүҲgave me\add* \add &this\add* messageВҰ321053 to tell them:
\v 13 Yisrael's godВҰ321067 YahwehВҰ321066 saysВҰ321065 that I personally madeВҰ321070 an agreementВҰ321071 with your ancestorsВҰ321074 on the dayВҰ321075 that I broughtВҰ321076 them out from \add вүҲtheir lives of slaveryВҰ321081 in\add* EgyptВҰ321079 \add (Heb. Mitsrayim)\add*. That was when I said that
\v 14 at the end of everyВҰ321088 sevenВҰ321085 years, you all mustВҰ321087 release any fellow HebrewsВҰ321092 who had sold \add #themselves\add* to you and servedВҰ321097 you for six years, \add вүҲreleasing them as free people\add*. \add вүҲHowever,\add* your ancestorsВҰ321106 did not listenВҰ321105 to me or \add вүҲshow any desire to obey\add* me.\x + \xo 34:14: \xt Exo 21:2; Deu 15:12.\x*
\v 15 \add вүҲNow\add* \add recently,\add* you yourselves repented andВҰ321114 began to do what \add вүҲI've said\add* is rightВҰ321120. You all madeВҰ321126 a solemn agreementВҰ321127 at my \add вүҲtemple that carries\add* my nameВҰ321133, that you'd \add вүҲmonitor each other\add* \add to free your slaves\add*.
\v 16 \add ButВҰ321136\add* then you all turnedВҰ321136 and profanedВҰ321137 my nameВҰ321140 \add вүҲby retrieving\add* your male and female slaves which you'd released as free \add >people\add*, and then forcedВҰ321155 them to \add вүҲwork as slaves again\add*,
\v 17 therefore Yahweh saysВҰ321166 this: You yourselves haven't listenedВҰ321171 to meвҖ”you all should have \add вүҲdeclared your fellow Israelis to be free\add*. \add So\add* listen, I'm aboutВҰ321180 to proclaimВҰ321180 вҖҳfreedomвҖҷ for you: freedom \add вүҲto experience war\add*, \add вүҲdeadly diseases\add*, and famineВҰ321194, \add вүҲbecause\add* I'm going to makeВҰ321195 you a horrible thing in the sight of every kingdomВҰ321200 \add вүҲin the world\add*. That is Yahweh'sВҰ321167 declaration.
\v 18 ThenВҰ321203 I'llВҰ321203 \add вүҲdeal with\add* the peopleВҰ321206 who've broken my agreement, who didn'tВҰ321212 \add вүҲrespect the intent\add* of the agreement thatВҰ321219 they established \add вүҲin front of\add* me when they cutВҰ321224 a bull in two andВҰ321203 walked betweenВҰ321227 the \add вүҲtwo halves\add*,
\v 19 \add вүҲwhen\add* the leaders of YehudahВҰ321231 and YerushalemВҰ321233, the \add вүҲofficials\add* and the priestsВҰ321235, and all the peopleВҰ321237 of the land walked betweenВҰ321240 the \add two\add* sections of the bull.
\v 20 I'llВҰ321244 \add вүҲhand them over to\add* their enemiesВҰ321247 and to thoseВҰ321249 who \add вүҲwant to see them dead\add*. Their bodies will be food for the birds in the skiesВҰ321255 and the animalsВҰ321256 on the ground.
\v 21 I'llВҰ321268 \add вүҲhand\add* Yehudah'sВҰ321264 KingВҰ321262 Tsidkiyah \add (ZedekiahВҰ321261)\add* and his leaders \add вүҲover\add* to their enemiesВҰ321270 and to thoseВҰ321272 who \add вүҲwant to see them dead\add*, and to the army of the Babylonian king who's \add вүҲattacking\add* you.
\v 22 This is Yahweh'sВҰ321285 declaration: Listen, I'm aboutВҰ321282 to roder them back to battle against this cityВҰ321289, and they'll captureВҰ321293 it and \add вүҲset it on fireВҰ321295\add*. Then I'llВҰ321286 makeВҰ321300 Yehudah'sВҰ321299 \add other\add* citiesВҰ321298 into \add вүҲdeserted\add* wastelandsВҰ321301.
\c 35
\s1 Praising the faithful Rekavites
\rem /s1 The Recabites; The Rechabites Commended; Jeremiah and the Rechabites; The Faithful Recabites
\p
\v 1 \add Several years earlier,\add* when Yehoyakim \add (Jehoiakim)\add* son of Yoshiyah \add (Josiah)\add* was the kingВҰ321320 of YehudahВҰ321321 \add (Judah)\add*, YahwehВҰ321314 \add вүҲhad given\add* Yirmeyah \add (Jeremiah)\add* this messageВҰ321306:\x + \xo 35:1: \xt 2Ki 23:36вҖ“24:6; 2Ch 36:5-7.\x*
\v 2 Go to the Rekavite clan and talk with them, then bringВҰ321331 them into one of the roomsВҰ321337 in my \add вүҲtemple\add*, and giveВҰ321338 them wine to drinkВҰ321338.
\v 3 \add вүҲSoВҰ321342\add* I tookВҰ321342 YaazanyahВҰ321345 (son of Yirmeyah, son of Havatsinyah) and his brothersВҰ321354 and his sons, and all the \add rest of\add* the Rekavite clan,
\v 4 andВҰ321366 I took them to the rooms of the sons of HananВҰ321374 (son of IgdalyahВҰ321377, manВҰ321378 of God) at the \add вүҲtemple\add*. Those rooms were besideВҰ321382 the leaders' room, which was aboveВҰ321386 the room of MaaseyahВҰ321388 (Shallum'sВҰ321391 son), the gatekeeper.
\v 5 ThenВҰ321395 I placed bowlsВҰ321402 and cups of wine in frontВҰ321396 of the Rekavites and told them to drinkВҰ321408 some.
\p
\v 6 \add вүҲButВҰ321412\add* they \add вүҲrespondedВҰ321412\add*, вҖңWe don'tВҰ321413 drink wine, becauseВҰ321417 our ancestorВҰ321422, Rekav's son Yonadav, commandedВҰ321423 \add all of\add* us andВҰ321412 our descendants not to ever drink any wine.
\v 7 \add вүЎHe also told us\add* not to buildВҰ321439 any housesВҰ321436, \add вүҲor to plantВҰ321447 any crops\add* or vineyardsВҰ321444, \add saying\add* that \add %we\add* mustВҰ321449 \add вүҲalways\add* liveВҰ321458 in tentsВҰ321452, so that \add %we'd\add* \add вүҲhave long lives in the land that we're staying in\add* \add as foreigners\add*.
\v 8 We've \add вүҲobeyed\add* the voiceВҰ321471 of our ancestorВҰ321476, Rekav's son Yonadav in everything that he commandedВҰ321479 us \add and\add* we, our wivesВҰ321488, and our children \add вүҲhave never drunk wine in our lives\add*.
\v 9 We'll never buildВҰ321493 housesВҰ321494 to live in, or \add вүҲown any\add* \add #vineyards, fieldsВҰ321497\add*, or seed.
\v 10 We've lived in tentsВҰ321505, andВҰ321504 we've \add вүҲfollowed everything\add* that ourВҰ321513 ancestorВҰ321513 Yonadav \add вүҲtoldВҰ321511\add* us,
\v 11 \add вүҲbutВҰ321515\add* when the Babylonian KingВҰ321518 NebuchadnezzarВҰ321517 attacked the land, we \add вүҲdecided that\add* we must \add вүҲmove\add* to Yerushalem to escape from the \add вүҲBabylonian\add* andВҰ321515 Aramean armies, so now we're \add all\add* living in Yerushalem.
\p
\v 12 Then YahwehВҰ321541 \add вүҲgave\add* this messageВҰ321539 to Yirmeyah, saying that
\v 13 Yisrael's godВҰ321552, Commander-in-chief Yahweh saysВҰ321549 to goВҰ321554 and \add вүҲask\add* the people in YehudahВҰ321557, includingВҰ321555 those who live in YerushalemВҰ321559: Won't youВҰ321555 all acceptВҰ321561 correctionВҰ321562 and listenВҰ321563 to my messages? This is Yahweh'sВҰ321550 declaration:
\v 14 Rekav's son Yonadav \add вүҲtoldВҰ321581\add* his descendants not to drinkВҰ321586 any wine \add вүҲand they've followed thatВҰ321579\add* to this very dayВҰ321593. \add вүҲIn contrast,\add* I've \add вүҲpersonally and consistently\add* spokenВҰ321601 to all of you \add вүҲbutВҰ321589 you haven't taken any notice of what I've said\add*.
\v 15 I \add вүҲpersistently\add* sentВҰ321609 all my servantsВҰ321615, the prophetsВҰ321616, out to you all to tell each person to turnВҰ321622 from their wicked \add >behaviour\add* and \add вүҲstart doing goodВҰ321628 instead\add*, and to \add вүҲstop following\add* afterВҰ321633 otherВҰ321635 godsВҰ321634 and serving them. ThenВҰ321609 they'd live on the land thatВҰ321641 I gaveВҰ321643 to your ancestorsВҰ321645 and to all of you, \add вүҲhowever, you all won'tВҰ321630 listenВҰ321652 to me or pay attention\add* to me.
\v 16 \add вүҲYes,\add* Yonadav's descendants have \add вүҲfollowed the instructionsВҰ321667\add* thatВҰ321666 their ancestorВҰ321665 gave them, butВҰ321668 this peopleВҰ321668, refuses to \add вүҲobey\add* me,
\v 17 \add вүҲso\add* Yisrael's god, Commander-in-chief YahwehВҰ321679, says this: Listen, I'm \add вүҲsending\add* all the disasters thatВҰ321698 I pronounced for YehudahВҰ321688, \add вүҲincludingВҰ321689\add* everyone living in YerushalemВҰ321693. \add вүЎI'm sending them\add* against them becauseВҰ321701 I spoke to them, but they wouldn't listenВҰ321705. I calledВҰ321706 to them, but they wouldn't answerВҰ321709.
\p
\v 18 ThenВҰ321711 Yirmeyah toldВҰ321740 the Rekavite clan that Yisrael's godВҰ321720, Commander-in-chief YahwehВҰ321718 saysВҰ321717 this: You've all listenedВҰ321724 to the commandsВҰ321735 of your ancestorВҰ321729 Yonadav andВҰ321711 have keptВҰ321730 them all. You've obeyed everything that he commanded you all to do,
\v 19 so Yisrael's godВҰ321749, Commander-in-chief YahwehВҰ321747 saysВҰ321746 this: There'll always be someone descended from Rekav's son Yonadav to serve me.
\c 36
\s1 Baruk reads out Yahweh's messages at the temple
\rem /s1 Jehoiakim Burns Jeremiah's Scroll; Baruch Reads the Scroll in the Temple; The Scroll Read in the Temple; Baruch Reads the Lord's Messages
\s4 Southern kingdom
\p
\v 1 In the fourthВҰ321768 yearВҰ321767 \add of the reign\add* Yehudah'sВҰ321774 KingВҰ321773 Yehoyakim (or Jehoiakim, son of Yoshiyah\add /Josiah\add*), YahwehВҰ321782 \add вүҲgave\add* this messageВҰ321776 to Yirmeyah:\x + \xo 36:1: \xt 2Ki 24:1; 2Ch 36:5-7; Dan 1:1-2.\x*
\v 2 Get a scrollВҰ321788 for yourselfВҰ321787 and writeВҰ321791 all the messages on it thatВҰ321797 I'veВҰ321799 told you concerning YisraelВҰ321803 and YehudahВҰ321806, and all the other nationsВҰ321811. Do this for everything I have said, \add back\add* from the \add вүҲtime\add* of Yoshiyah until \add вүҲthe present time\add*.
\v 3 PerhapsВҰ321821 Yehudah'sВҰ321824 \add вүҲpeople\add* will hearВҰ321822 about all the disasters thatВҰ321829 I intend to bring on them and then turnВҰ321835 away from \add #their\add* wicked \add #ways\add*, so I can forgiveВҰ321839 them for their wickedness and their disobedience.
\p
\v 4 Then Yirmeyah calledВҰ321844 Neriyah's son Baruk, and Yirmeyah dictated all the messages thatВҰ321861 YahwehВҰ321860 had \add вүҲgiven\add* to him, for Baruk to \add вүҲrecord\add* on a scrollВҰ321867.
\v 5 ThenВҰ321871 Yirmeyah \add вүҲinstructedВҰ321871\add* Baruk saying, вҖңI'm restrained \add вүҲfrom entering\add* Yahweh'sВҰ321883 \add вүҲresidence\add*
\v 6 \add вүҲso\add* you must go andВҰ321885 read from the scrollВҰ321888 that you wroteВҰ321891 at my dictation. On the dayВҰ321902 of the fast, you must read Yahweh'sВҰ321897 messages so that all the people in the \add вүҲtemple will hear them\add* as well as the \add people from\add* the rest of Yehudah'sВҰ321908 citiesВҰ321910. Proclaim these messages to them.
\v 7 Perhaps Yaweh \add вүҲwill take notice of\add* their \add вүҲpleas for mercy\add*. Perhaps everyoneВҰ321919 will turnВҰ321918 from their wicked \add #ways\add*, since the angerВҰ321925 and fury thatВҰ321927 YahwehВҰ321917 has proclaimed againstВҰ321931 this \add вүҲnation\add* is severe.
\v 8 \add вүҲSoВҰ321936\add* Neriyah's son Baruk did everything that the prophetВҰ321946 Yirmeyah had \add вүҲtoldВҰ321944\add* him toвҖ”he read Yahweh's messages aloud at Yahweh's \add вүҲtemple\add*.
\p
\v 9 In the ninthВҰ321966 monthВҰ321965 of the \add вүҲnext\add* year, all the people in YerushalemВҰ321974 and the \add вүҲvisitors to the city from the rest of\add* YehudahВҰ321964, announced a fast \add вүҲto honour\add* YahwehВҰ321970.
\v 10 \add вүҲAgain\add* Baruk read Yirmeyah's messages aloud at Yahweh's \add вүҲtemple\add*, from the roomВҰ321992 of GemaryahВҰ321993 (son of the scribeВҰ321997 ShafanВҰ321996) in the upperВҰ321999 courtyardВҰ321998, by the entranceВҰ322000 gateВҰ322001 to Yahweh's \add вүҲresidence\add*. He did this \add вүҲso that all the peopleВҰ322009 could hear it\add*.
\s1 The messages get read to the officials
\rem /s1 The Scroll Read in the Palace; The Scroll Is Read to the Officials
\s4 Southern kingdom
\p
\v 11 \add вүҲWhenВҰ322011\add* MikayahВҰ322012 (son of GemaryahВҰ322015 son of ShafanВҰ322018) heard all Yahweh'sВҰ322024 messasges from the scrollВҰ322026,
\v 12 he went down to to the \add вүҲsecretary's\add* room in the \add вүҲpalace\add*, and wow, all the officials were sittingВҰ322042 thereВҰ322038: Elishama the \add вүҲsecretary\add*, Shemayah'sВҰ322048 son DelayahВҰ322045, Akbor's son ElnatanВҰ322049, Shafan'sВҰ322056 son GemaryahВҰ322053, and Hananyah'sВҰ322060 son Tsidkiyah, \add вүҲalong with\add* all the \add other\add* officials.
\v 13 \add вүҲWhenВҰ322065\add* Mikayah reported to them all the messages thatВҰ322072 he'd heardВҰ322073 Baruk read aloudВҰ322074 \add вүҲfor the peopleВҰ322078 to hear\add*,
\v 14 the officials sent Yehudi (son of Netanyah son of ShelemyahВҰ322095 son of Kushi) to Baruk. Yehudi \add вүҲordered\add* Baruk, вҖңTake the scroll in your hand, the scroll from whichВҰ322101 you were reading in the hearing of the peopleВҰ322105, and come.вҖқ \add вүҲSoВҰ322080\add* Neriyah's son Baruk took the scroll and went to the officials
\v 15 \add вүҲwhere\add* they told him to sitВҰ322123 down andВҰ322121 read it \add вүҲto them\add*, \add вүҲso\add* BarukВҰ322128 \add вүҲread out\add* \add the messages\add*.
\v 16 \add вүҲWhenВҰ322146\add* they heardВҰ322132 \add вүҲit all\add*, they \add вүҲwere afraid andВҰ322131 decided together that they needed to report it\add* all to the kingВҰ322149,
\v 17 andВҰ322156 theyВҰ322159 askedВҰ322159 Baruk, вҖңHow come youВҰ322166 wrote down all theseВҰ322172 messages from Yirmeyah?вҖқ
\p
\v 18 вҖңHe dictated them to me,вҖқ he replied, вҖңandВҰ322175 I \add вүҲjust wrote them down\add* on the scrollВҰ322190.вҖқ
\p
\v 19 Then the officialsВҰ322195 told Baruk, вҖңGo \add and\add* hideВҰ322200, and Yirmeyah \add as well\add*. Don'tВҰ322204 let anyoneВҰ322203 knowВҰ322206 whereВҰ322207 youВҰ322201 two are.вҖқ
\s1 King Yehoyakim burns the scroll
\rem /s1 The King Burns the Scroll; Jehoiakim Burns the Scroll
\s4 Southern kingdom
\p
\v 20 ThenВҰ322210 they left the scrollВҰ322217 in the secretary Elishama'sВҰ322220 room and wentВҰ322210 out to the king in the courtyardВҰ322214 and told him everything \add they'd heard\add*.
\rem /s1 King Jehoiakim Burns the Scroll
\v 21 The king sent Yehudi to get the scrollВҰ322238, and he went and got it from the secretary Elishama's room. ThenВҰ322230 Yehudi read it \add вүҲaloudВҰ322243\add* for the king and all the officialsВҰ322250 who were standingВҰ322251 beside him \add вүҲto hear\add*.
\v 22 \add *That\add* monthВҰ322259, the kingВҰ322255 was in his winterВҰ322258 houseВҰ322257 andВҰ322261 a brazier was burning in front of himВҰ322264.
\v 23 \add вүҲWhenever\add* YehudiВҰ322270 had read \add вүҲa couple\add* of columns, the king would \add вүҲslice it off\add* with a knifeВҰ322275 andВҰ322267 toss it into the fire untilВҰ322285 the entireВҰ322288 scrollВҰ322290 was gone,
\v 24 \add вүҲbutВҰ322299\add* neither the kingВҰ322306 or any of his servantsВҰ322309 were afraidВҰ322300 of the messages (andВҰ322299 they didn'tВҰ322299 tear theirВҰ322305 clothesВҰ322305 \add to indicate repentance\add*вҖ”
\v 25 ElnatanВҰ322318, DelayahВҰ322319, andВҰ322317 GemaryahВҰ322320 had urged the kingВҰ322322 not to burnВҰ322324 the scrollВҰ322327, butВҰ322317 he \add вүҲhadn't taken any notice of\add* them).
\v 26 ThenВҰ322332 the king orderedВҰ322332 a \add вүҲrelative\add* Yerahme'el, Azriel'sВҰ322345 son SerayahВҰ322342, and Abdeel'sВҰ322351 son ShelemyahВҰ322348 to arrest the scribeВҰ322356 Baruk and the prophetВҰ322359 Yirmeyah, butВҰ322332 YahwehВҰ322361 had hidden them.
\s1 Yirmeyah rewrites the scroll
\rem /s1 Jeremiah Writes Another Scroll; Jeremiah Dictates Another; Jeremiah Rewrites the Scroll
\s4 Southern kingdom
\p
\v 27 After the kingВҰ322374 had burntВҰ322373 the scrollВҰ322377 with the messages on it thatВҰ322381 Yirmeyah had dictated to Baruk, YahwehВҰ322367 \add вүҲgave this\add* messageВҰ322365 to Yirmeyah:
\v 28 Get yourselfВҰ322391 anotherВҰ322393 scroll and writeВҰ322394 down all the messages that were on the original scroll that Yehudah'sВҰ322412 KingВҰ322410 Yehoyakim \add (Jehoiakim)\add* burntВҰ322408.
\v 29 ThenВҰ322414 you mustВҰ322420 tell \add @the king\add* that YahwehВҰ322423 says: You burntВҰ322425 that scrollВҰ322428, asking why it was written that the Babylonian king would come and destroyВҰ322441 this land and leave it without people or animalsВҰ322449.
\v 30 \add вүҲNow\add* YahwehВҰ322456 saysВҰ322455 about KingВҰ322460 Yehoyakim: No descendant of his will ever sit on David'sВҰ322471 throneВҰ322470. As for him, his corpseВҰ322472 will be thrownВҰ322474 out into the heat of the dayВҰ322476 and the frostВҰ322477 at nightВҰ322478.
\v 31 I'll punish him, his descendants, and his servantsВҰ322487 for theirВҰ322490 \add вүҲwickedness\add*. The disasters thatВҰ322505 I'veВҰ322507 threatened them with, \add вүҲbutВҰ322480 whichВҰ322505\add* theyВҰ322510 \add ^ignored\add*, I'll \add вүҲsend\add* onto them and all Yerushalem'sВҰ322496 inhabitantsВҰ322495, and onto everyВҰ322499 person in \add the rest of\add* YehudahВҰ322500.
\p
\v 32 \add вүҲSo\add* Yirmeyah got anotherВҰ322517 scroll and gave it to Baruk, son of Neriyah the scribeВҰ322525. Yirmeyah \add againВҰ322542\add* dictated all the messages thatВҰ322535 had been on the scroll burntВҰ322536 by Yehudah'sВҰ322540 KingВҰ322538 Yehoyakim, and Baruk wroteВҰ322526 them onto the scoll, \add вүҲalong with several\add* other similar messages.
\c 37
\s1 Yirmeyah's response to Tsidkiyah/Zedekiah
\rem /s1 Zedekiah's Request to Jeremiah; Jeremiah in Prison; Zedekiah Calls for Jeremiah; Zedekiah's Vain Hope
\s4 Southern kingdom
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲBy now\add* Yoshiyah's son Tsidkiyah \add (ZedekiahВҰ322553)\add* reignedВҰ322550 as king instead of Yehoyakim's son Yehoyakin. The Babylonian KingВҰ322552 NebuchadnezzarВҰ322564 had made Tsidkiyah king over the YehudahВҰ322569 \add вүҲregionВҰ322568\add*.\x + \xo 37:1: \xt 2Ki 24:17; 2Ch 36:10.\x*
\v 2 \add вүҲHowever,\add* \add @Tsidkiyah\add*, his servantsВҰ322574, andВҰ322571 his peopleВҰ322575 wouldn't listenВҰ322572 to Yahweh'sВҰ322580 messages thatВҰ322581 he'd \add вүҲgiven\add* via the prophetВҰ322585 Yirmeyah.
\p
\v 3 \add вүҲEventually,\add* KingВҰ322588 Tsidkiyah, Shelemyah'sВҰ322595 son Yehukal, andВҰ322587 Tsefanyah son of MaaseyahВҰ322601 the priestВҰ322602, sentВҰ322587 a message to the prophetВҰ322606 Yirmeyah \add вүҲrequesting him\add*, вҖңPray on our behalf to our godВҰ322615, YahwehВҰ322614.
\v 4 \add вүҲAt that time,\add* Yirmeyah was \add still\add* comingВҰ322618 andВҰ322617 goingВҰ322619 among the peopleВҰ322621, because he hadn't yet been put in prison.
\v 5 Far'oh's \add (Pharaoh'sВҰ322631)\add* army had comeВҰ322632 out of EgyptВҰ322633, and the \add вүҲBabylonians\add* who were besieging Yerushalem heardВҰ322634 the \add вүҲnewsВҰ322642\add* about them and \add вүҲretreated from\add* Yerushalem.
\p
\v 6 Then YahwehВҰ322651 \add вүҲgave\add* Yirmeyah this messageВҰ322649 to proclaim:
\v 7 Yisrael's godВҰ322662, YahwehВҰ322661 told me thatВҰ322679 you \add >people\add* should sayВҰ322666 this to Yehudah'sВҰ322670 kingВҰ322669 who sentВҰ322671 you all to consultВҰ322674 me: Listen Far'oh's army whichВҰ322679 was comingВҰ322679 out to helpВҰ322681 you all is aboutВҰ322682 to returnВҰ322682 back to itsВҰ322683 own \add вүҲcountry\add*, EgyptВҰ322684.
\v 8 ThenВҰ322686 the \add вүҲBabyloniansВҰ322687\add* will returnВҰ322686 and attack this cityВҰ322691, thenВҰ322686 they'll captureВҰ322693 it and burnВҰ322694 it \add вүҲdown\add*.
\v 9 YahwehВҰ322701 saysВҰ322700 not to deceiveВҰ322704 yourselves that the BabyloniansВҰ322710 have left, becauseВҰ322711 they won'tВҰ322702 leave,
\v 10 because even if you all defeatedВҰ322719 the entireВҰ322720 BabylonianВҰ322723 army that's attacking you so that only wounded menВҰ322728 were left in their tents, they would get up and burnВҰ322733 \add вүҲdown\add* this cityВҰ322736.
\s1 Yirmeyah is arrested and imprisoned
\rem /s1 Jeremiah Is Arrested and Imprisoned; Jeremiah Is Imprisoned
\s4 Southern kingdom
\p
\v 11 ThenВҰ322740 when the Babylonian army had left YerushalemВҰ322745 \add вүҲto avoid\add* Far'oh's army,
\v 12 Yirmeyah left \add *the city\add* to goВҰ322754 to the BenyaminВҰ322756 \add вүҲregionВҰ322755\add* to \add вүҲtake possession of a section\add* \add of landВҰ322755\add* thereВҰ322758 among \add &his\add* peopleВҰ322760.
\v 13 \add вүҲAs he went through\add* the BenyaminВҰ322766 gateВҰ322765, a chief guardВҰ322769 named Yiriyah (son of ShelemyahВҰ322774, son of HananyahВҰ322777) was thereВҰ322767. He seized the prophetВҰ322782 Yirmeyah andВҰ322762 \add вүҲclaimed that\add* he was deserting to the \add вүҲBabylonians\add*.
\p
\v 14 \add вүҲButВҰ322790\add* Yirmeyah \add вүҲdisputed\add*, вҖңThat's a lieвҖ”I'm not deserting to the \add вүҲBabylonians\add*.вҖқ \add вүҲHowever\add* Yiriyah wouldn't listenВҰ322799 to him and he \add вүҲarrested\add* him and took him to the officialsВҰ322807.
\v 15 The officialsВҰ322810 were angryВҰ322809 at Yirmeyah and they \add had\add* him beaten and put in prison. (\add The place\add* had been the house of the scribeВҰ322822 Yonatan, butВҰ322809 it had been converted into \add вүҲa prison\add*.)
\v 16 \add вүҲSo\add* Yirmeyah was \add вүҲkept thereВҰ322842\add* in an \add вүҲunderground cell\add* for \add вүҲseveral\add* daysВҰ322844.
\p
\v 17 Then KingВҰ322849 Tsidkiyah sent \add >someone\add* to fetch \add @Yirmeyah\add*, and in his houseВҰ322854, the king \add вүҲaskedВҰ322852\add* him privately, вҖңIs there any messageВҰ322858 from YahwehВҰ322860?вҖқ
\p вҖңThere is a messsage,вҖқ Jeremiah \add вүҲanswered\add*. вҖңYou'll be \add вүҲhanded over\add* to the Babylonian king.вҖқ
\v 18 Then Yirmeyah asked \add *the kingВҰ322876\add*, вҖңWhat \add вүҲcrime have I committed against\add* you or your servantsВҰ322881 or your peopleВҰ322882, that you've \add вүҲhad me put in prison\add*?
\v 19 Where are \add вүҲall the other\add* prophets who prophesiedВҰ322898 to you all that the Babylonian kingВҰ322904 wouldn't comeВҰ322903 \add вүҲhere\add*?
\v 20 \add вүҲButВҰ322912\add* now, my masterВҰ322916 the kingВҰ322917, please listenВҰ322913 \add вүҲto this appeal\add*: Don'tВҰ322923 return me to the scribeВҰ322928 Yonatan'sВҰ322927 houseВҰ322926, or I'llВҰ322930 dieВҰ322930 thereВҰ322931.вҖқ
\p
\v 21 \add вүҲSoВҰ322933\add* KingВҰ322934 Tsidkiyah orderedВҰ322933 that Yirmeyah \add вүҲbe held\add* in the guards' courtyard, andВҰ322933 he was given a loaf of bread every day from the bakers' streetВҰ322948, untilВҰ322950 \add the time\add* when all the bread in the city \add вүҲran out\add*. \add вүҲButВҰ322933\add* Yirmeyah remained \add confined\add* in the guards's courtyard.
\c 38
\s1 Yirmeyah is placed down a shaft
\rem /s1 Jeremiah in a Cistern; Jeremiah Thrown Into a Cistern; Jeremiah in the Cistern; Jeremiah in a Dry Well
\s4 Southern kingdom
\p
\v 1 \add Four officials,\add* Mattan'sВҰ322968 son Shefatyah, Pashhur'sВҰ322972 son GedalyahВҰ322969, Shelemyah'sВҰ322976 son Yehukal, andВҰ322964 Malkiyah'sВҰ322980 son Pashhur heard the messages thatВҰ322984 Yirmeyah was telling all the peopleВҰ322991, saying:
\v 2 YahwehВҰ322997 saysВҰ322996 this: AnyoneВҰ322998 who stays in this cityВҰ322999 will be killed by \add вүҲfighting\add*, famineВҰ323003, or \add вүҲdeadly diseases\add*, \add вүҲbutВҰ323004\add* anyoneВҰ322998 who goesВҰ323005 out to the \add вүҲBabyloniansВҰ323008\add* will \add вүҲsurviveвҖ”they won't be killed\add*.
\v 3 YahwehВҰ323021 saysВҰ323020 that this cityВҰ323024 will definitely \add вүҲbe taken over and capturedВҰ323031\add* by the BabylonianВҰ323030 kingВҰ323028.
\p
\v 4 \add вүҲSoВҰ323033\add* \add &those\add* officialsВҰ323034 went to \add @King Tsidkiyah\add* \add вүҲand requested that Yirmeyah be executed\add* becauseВҰ323044 \add (they claimed)\add* his messages were \add вүҲdiscouraging\add* their warriorsВҰ323055 \add вүҲdefending\add* the cityВҰ323059 and \add вүЎdiscouraging\add* all the people. \add вүЎThey claimed\add* that he wasn't \add вүҲadvancing\add* the people's safety, butВҰ323033 \add causing\add* harm.
\p
\v 5 вҖң\add вүҲAll right\add*,вҖқ KingВҰ323085 Tsidkiyah \add вүҲreplied\add*. вҖң\add вүҲDo whatever you want with him\add*, becauseВҰ323091 no king \add вүҲcan argue against all of\add* you.вҖқ
\v 6 \add вүҲSoВҰ323099\add* they took Yirmeyah and \add вүҲput\add* him into the \add water storage\add* cistern \add carved out by\add* the king's son MalkiyahВҰ323109. It was \add right thereВҰ323122\add* in the guards' courtyardВҰ323114, and they lowered Yirmeyah down with ropesВҰ323120. There wasn't any water \add left\add* in the cistern, butВҰ323099 it was \add still\add* muddy \add at the bottom\add* and he sank down into the mud.
\rem /s1 Jeremiah Is Rescued by Ebed-melech
\p
\v 7 \add вүҲNow\add* the Kushite Eved-MelekВҰ323137 was one of the \add вүҲtrusted servants\add* in the king's houseВҰ323142 and he heard that they had put Yirmeyah down into the cisternВҰ323152. \add вүҲMeanwhile,\add* the king was sittingВҰ323154 at the BenyaminВҰ323156 Gate.
\v 8 \add вүҲSoВҰ323158\add* EvedВҰ323159-MelekВҰ323161 left the \add вүҲpalace\add* and \add вүҲwent and spokeВҰ323164 with\add* the king,
\v 9 вҖңMy masterВҰ323170 the kingВҰ323171, those menВҰ323173 have been evilВҰ323172 in the way they've mistreated the prophetВҰ323181 Yirmeyah. They threw him into a cisternВҰ323188 so he'd die in it from hunger, since there's no food left in the cityВҰ323197.вҖқ
\v 10 ThenВҰ323199 the king orderedВҰ323199 Eved-MelekВҰ323204 to takeВҰ323207 commandВҰ323199 of thirtyВҰ323210 of \add the king's menВҰ323211\add* to go andВҰ323199 get the prophetВҰ323216 Yirmeyah out of the cisternВҰ323219 \add вүҲso he wouldn't dieВҰ323221\add* \add down there\add*.
\v 11 \add вүҲSoВҰ323223\add* Eved-MelekВҰ323227 \add вүҲled\add* the menВҰ323230 to a storeroomВҰ323239 for clothing underВҰ323238 the king's houseВҰ323233 where they got some rags andВҰ323223 worn-out clothes. ThenВҰ323223 they let them down by ropesВҰ323254 to Yirmeyah in the cisternВҰ323253
\v 12 and \add вүҲtold him to use the rags and old clothesВҰ323267 under his armpits to protect him from being hurt by\add* the ropesВҰ323273. Yirmeyah did that,
\v 13 thenВҰ323278 they pulled him up with the ropesВҰ323282вҖ”\add вүҲthat's how they got him up out\add* from the \add mud in\add* the cisternВҰ323287. ThenВҰ323278 he stayed in the guards' courtyardВҰ323290.
\s1 King Tsidkiyah's advice to Yirmeyah
\rem /s1 Zedekiah Consults Jeremiah Again; Zedekiah Asks Jeremiah's Advice; Zedekiah Questions Jeremiah Again; Zedekiah Questions Jeremiah
\s4 Southern kingdom
\p
\v 14 \add вүҲOne day\add* KingВҰ323295 Tsidkiyah \add (ZedekiahВҰ323296)\add* \add вүҲsummoned\add* the prophetВҰ323301 Yirmeyah \add вүҲto meet him\add* at the thirdВҰ323306 entranceВҰ323305 to \add вүҲthe temple\add* and told him, вҖңI want to askВҰ323315 youВҰ323317 something. Don'tВҰ323319 \add вүҲrefuse to answer honestly and truthfully\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 15 вҖң\add Ha,\add* if I tell you the truth, you'll order me to be executed,вҖқ Yirmeyah \add вүҲreplied\add*. вҖңAnd if I give you good advice, you won'tВҰ323333 \add вүҲtake any notice of\add* what I say.вҖқ
\p
\v 16 \add вүҲButВҰ323342\add* KingВҰ323343 Tsidkiyah privately promised Yirmeyah, вҖңAs \add вүҲour creatorВҰ323361\add* YahwehВҰ323352 lives, I won't execute you or \add вүҲhandВҰ323369 you over to\add* those menВҰ323370 who \add вүҲwant to see you dead\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 17 вҖң\add Okay,\add*вҖқ Yirmeyah \add вүҲanswered\add* \add *the king\add*, вҖңYisrael's god, Commander-in-chief YahwehВҰ323387 says this: If you indeedВҰ323394 go out to the Babylonian king's officials, then you'll live, and this cityВҰ323404 won'tВҰ323406 be burntВҰ323407 \add down\add*. You and your family would live.
\v 18 ButВҰ323413 if you don'tВҰ323414 goВҰ323416 out to \add *his\add* officials, thenВҰ323413 this cityВҰ323423 will be \add вүҲhanded over to the Babylonians\add*. They'll burnВҰ323427 it \add down\add*, andВҰ323413 you wouldn't \add be able to\add* escapeВҰ323432 from theirВҰ323433 \add вүҲpower\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 19 вҖң\add ButВҰ323436\add* I'm afraid of the \add вүҲJudaneans\add* who've \add already\add* deserted to the Babylonians,вҖқ \add *the kingВҰ323437\add* \add вүҲconfided to\add* Yirmeyah. вҖң\add вүҲYou see,\add* I might be \add вүҲhanded over to them\add* and they \add вүҲmight treat me cruelly\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 20 вҖң\add @The Babylonians\add* won'tВҰ323464 \add вүҲhand\add*e you over to \add @those Jews\add*,вҖқ Yirmeyah \add вүҲrespondedВҰ323462\add*. вҖңObey Yahweh'sВҰ323471 message from Yahweh that I'm \add вүҲpassing on to\add* you, so that things will goВҰ323476 well for you, and so that you'll liveВҰ323478 \add through this\add*.
\v 21 \add вүҲHowever,\add* if youВҰ323484 refuseВҰ323483 to \add вүҲsurrender\add*, thenВҰ323481 this is what YahwehВҰ323490 has shownВҰ323489 me:
\v 22 Listen king of YehudahВҰ323501, all the women who are left in your \add вүҲpalace\add* will be taken out to the Babylonian king's commandersВҰ323505. Those women will tell you,
\q1 вҖҳYou were deceived by your friendsвҖ”they've ruined you.
\q1 Now your feetВҰ323517 are \add вүҲstuck\add* in the mud, andВҰ323492 your friends have turnedВҰ323518 away.вҖҷ
\p
\v 23 \add вүҲYes,\add* all your wivesВҰ323525 and childrenВҰ323528 will be taken out to the \add вүҲBabylonians\add* and you yourself won'tВҰ323534 escapeВҰ323536 from \add вүҲthem\add* \add either\add*. You'll be taken captive by the Babylonian kingВҰ323540, and this cityВҰ323546 will be burnt \add down\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 24 Then Tsidkiyah told Yirmeyah, вҖңDon'tВҰ323558 \add вүҲtell anyoneВҰ323557 else what we spoke about or youВҰ323565 might\add* dieВҰ323565.
\v 25 If the officialsВҰ323570 hear that I'veВҰ323573 have talked with you, and if they come and \add вүҲdemand\add*, вҖҳTell us what you said to the kingвҖ”don'tВҰ323589 hideВҰ323591 it from us or we'll kill you,вҖҷ
\v 26 thenВҰ323601 you mustВҰ323601 tell them, вҖҳI \add вүҲwas just pleading\add* to the king not to return me to \add the dungeon in\add* Yonatan's houseВҰ323611 \add вүҲor I'd\add* die thereВҰ323614.вҖҷвҖҜ
\v 27 Then \add sure enough\add* the officialsВҰ323620 cameВҰ323617 to Yirmeyah and questioned him and he \add вүҲanswered\add* them as the kingВҰ323634 had \add вүҲinstructedВҰ323633\add* him. They couldn't say anything else becauseВҰ323637 they hadn't heardВҰ323640 the \add вүҲconversation\add*,
\v 28 \add вүҲso\add* Yirmeyah remained in the guards' courtyardВҰ323646 untilВҰ323648 the dayВҰ323650 that YerushalemВҰ323654 was captured.\x + \xo 38:28: \xt Eze 33:21.\x*
\c 39
\s1 The fall of Yerushalem
\rem /s1 The Fall of Jerusalem
\s4 Southern kingdom
\p
\v 1 In the tenthВҰ323669 monthВҰ323668 of the ninthВҰ323663 yearВҰ323662 \add of the reign\add* of Yehudah'sВҰ323667 King Tsidkiyah \add (ZedekiahВҰ323664)\add*, the Babylonian King NebuchadnezzarВҰ323671 cameВҰ323670 against YerushalemВҰ323680 with his \add вүҲlarge\add* army and besieged itВҰ323682.
\v 2 On the ninth dayВҰ323692 of the fourthВҰ323691 month of Tsidkiyah's eleventh yearВҰ323688,\f + \fr 39:2 \ft i.e., about eighteen months later (in 586 B.C.).\f* the cityВҰ323695 was brokenВҰ323694 into.
\v 3 ThenВҰ323697 all of the Babylonian king's officials came and sat at the middleВҰ323705 gateВҰ323704, \add includingВҰ323703\add* the top official Nevu-Sarsekim, and SamgarВҰ323710-Nevu and Sarsekim.
\p
\v 4 WhenВҰ323733 Yehudah'sВҰ323739 KingВҰ323737 Tsidkiyah and all his warriorsВҰ323742 sawВҰ323735 \add what was happening\add*, they \add left\add* at nighttimeВҰ323746 through the gateВҰ323753 betweenВҰ323754 the twoВҰ323755 wallsВҰ323755 beside the king's gardenВҰ323751 and fledВҰ323744 towards the Yarden river plains.
\v 5 \add вүҲHowever\add* the \add вүҲBabylonian\add* army chased afterВҰ323764 them and overtookВҰ323765 the kingВҰ323777 down in the plainsВҰ323769 near Yeriho \add (Jericho)\add*. They took him back up to the Babylonian KingВҰ323777 NebuchadnezzarВҰ323776 at Rivlah in the HamatВҰ323782 \add вүҲregionВҰ323781\add*, and he pronounced \add &his\add* judgementВҰ323785 on him.
\v 6 The king had Tsidkiyah's sons slaughtered at Rivlah as \add @their father\add* \add was forced to\add* watch, andВҰ323787 Yehudah'sВҰ323800 officials were also executed.
\v 7 ThenВҰ323805 they \add вүҲgouged out\add* out Tsidkiyah'sВҰ323808 eyesВҰ323807 andВҰ323810 put himВҰ323810 in chains to be taken to BabylonВҰ323814.
\v 8 ThenВҰ323816 the BabyloniansВҰ323825 burntВҰ323824 down the \add вүҲpalace\add* and the \add вүҲother\add* houses, and tore down Yerushalem'sВҰ323830 wallsВҰ323829.
\v 9 The rest of the people who'd stayed in the cityВҰ323837, includingВҰ323838 thoseВҰ323840 who'd \add вүҲpreviously\add* deserted, were exiledВҰ323848 to BabylonВҰ323856 \add under the supervision of\add* the chiefВҰ323853 bodyguardВҰ323855 Nevuzar-Adan.
\v 10 \add вүҲHoweverВҰ323868,\add* \add *he\add* allowed the poorest peopleВҰ323860 who didn'tВҰ323863 own anythingВҰ323866 to remain in YehudahВҰ323873вҖ”allocating vineyardsВҰ323876 andВҰ323858 fieldsВҰ323877 \add for them to work\add*.
\s1 Yirmeyah is released
\rem /s1 Jeremiah, Set Free, Remembers Ebed-melech; Jeremiah's Release; Jeremiah Remains in Judah
\p
\v 11 \add вүҲNow\add* the Babylonian KingВҰ323883 NebuchadnezzarВҰ323882 had given an order to his chiefВҰ323891 bodyguardВҰ323893 Nevuzar-Adan about \add finding\add* Yirmeyah
\v 12 and keeping him safe and unharmedвҖ”even to care for him and do anythingВҰ323904 that he requested.
\v 13 \add вүҲSoВҰ323916\add* Nevuzar-Adan, the top servant Nevu-Shazban, the high official Nergal-Sharezer, andВҰ323916 all the Babylonian king's most important officials
\v 14 sentВҰ323939 out men to fetch Yirmeyah from the guards' courtyardВҰ323944. They \add вүҲhanded him over\add* to GedalyahВҰ323950 (son of AhikamВҰ323953, son of ShafanВҰ323956) to takeВҰ323957 him home, \add вүҲso\add* Yirmeyah stayed \add there\add* among the peopleВҰ323963.
\s1 The hope of Ibid-Milik
\rem /s1 Hope for Ebedmelech
\p
\v 15 \add вүҲWhile\add* Yirmeyah had still been \add вүҲheld\add*in the guards' courtyardВҰ323975, YahwehВҰ323972 had given him this messageВҰ323970:
\v 16 Go and tell Eved-Melek the \add вүҲEthiopian\add* that Yisrael's godВҰ323992, Commander-in-chief YahwehВҰ323990 saysВҰ323989 this: Listen, I'm aboutВҰ323995 to \add вүҲfulfill\add* my messages againstВҰ324000 this cityВҰ324002 for disaster and not for goodВҰ324006, and they'll all come true \add вүҲright in frontВҰ324008 of yourВҰ324008 eyes\add* on that dayВҰ324009.
\v 17 \add вүҲButВҰ324012\add* YahwehВҰ324018 declares that I'llВҰ324012 rescueВҰ324012 you from those peopleВҰ324022 that you'reВҰ324025 afraid of
\v 18 because I'llВҰ324031 definitely save your life. You won'tВҰ324033 \add вүҲbe killed by the soldiers\add*, butВҰ324032 YahwehВҰ324045 declares that because you put your trustВҰ324041 in me, your life will be saved.
\c 40
\s1 Yirmeyah returns to Gedalyah
\rem /s1 Jeremiah Freed; Jeremiah Stays with Gedaliah; After the capture of Jerusalem; Jeremiah with Gedaliah the Governor
\s4 Southern kingdom
\p
\v 1 The chiefВҰ324062 bodyguardВҰ324064 Nevuzar-Adan had found Yirmeyah \add вүҲchainedВҰ324073 up\add* among all the exilesВҰ324077 from YerushalemВҰ324078 and \add the rest of\add* Yehudah to be takenВҰ324080 to BabylonВҰ324081, and had released him at RamahВҰ324067.
\p
\v 2 The chiefВҰ324084 bodyguardВҰ324086 tookВҰ324083 Yirmeyah \add aside\add* andВҰ324088 told him, вҖңYour godВҰ324091 YahwehВҰ324090 decreed this disaster for this placeВҰ324099,
\v 3 thenВҰ324102 he caused it to happen. YahwehВҰ324104 did just as he'd decreed, since you \add >people\add* sinnedВҰ324109 against him andВҰ324102 didn'tВҰ324111 obey \add вүҲhim\add*. That'sВҰ324110 why \add all\add* this has happened to you people.
\v 4 \add вүҲButВҰ324121\add* now listen, I'veВҰ324123 released you today from your chainsВҰ324127. If \add вүҲyou choose\add* to come with me to BabylonВҰ324138, I'llВҰ324140 \add вүҲlook after\add* you, \add вүҲbutВҰ324121 if you don't want to\add*, thenВҰ324121 look \add вүҲaround\add* andВҰ324121 go \add вүҲwherever you think best\add*.
\v 5 \add ?вүҲOr why don'tВҰ324171 you return\add* to GedalyahВҰ324177 (son of AhikamВҰ324180, son of ShafanВҰ324183) who the Babylonian king has put in charge of Yehudah'sВҰ324190 citiesВҰ324189. Stay among the peopleВҰ324194 with him, or go wherever \add вүҲyou think best\add*.вҖқ ThenВҰ324170 the the king's chiefВҰ324207 bodyguardВҰ324209 gaveВҰ324204 him food and a gift, and sent him away.
\v 6 \add вүҲSoВҰ324214\add* Yirmeyah wentВҰ324214 to Gedalyah'sВҰ324218 \add place\add* andВҰ324223 stayed with him among the peopleВҰ324226 who were left behind in the land.
\s1 Yehudah's governor Gedalyah
\rem /s1 Gedaliah Assassinated; Gedaliah, Governor of Judah; Gedaliah Governs in Judah
\s4 Southern kingdom
\r (2 Kgs 25:22-24)
\p
\v 7 \add вүҲNow some\add* commandersВҰ324234 of \add Judean\add* \add вүҲsoldiers\add* who were still in the countrysideВҰ324237, along with theirВҰ324239 men heard that the Babylonian kingВҰ324243 had made Ahikam'sВҰ324251 son GedalyahВҰ324248 governor over the land. They also heard that he'd put him in charge of the men, womenВҰ324258, and children who were the poorest peopleВҰ324260 in the landвҖ”thoseВҰ324262 who hadn't been exiledВҰ324265 to BabylonВҰ324245.\x + \xo 40:7-9: \xt 2Ki 25:22-24.\x*
\v 8 \add вүҲSoВҰ324268\add* they went to GedalyahВҰ324271 at Mitspah. Those \add вүҲwho went\add* were Netanyah's son YishmaelВҰ324273, Kareah'sВҰ324281 sons YohananВҰ324277 and Yonatan, Tanhumet'sВҰ324285 son SerayahВҰ324282, the sons of Ofai the Netofatite, and Maakati's son YezanyahВҰ324291, and theirВҰ324296 menВҰ324296.
\v 9 GedalyahВҰ324300 (son of AhikamВҰ324303, son of ShafanВҰ324306) \add made a promise\add* to them and theirВҰ324307 menВҰ324307, saying, вҖңDon'tВҰ324309 be afraidВҰ324311 to serve the \add вүҲBabylonian\add* officials. Live in the land and serve the Babylonian kingВҰ324319, and it will goВҰ324321 well with you.
\v 10 See, I'm livingВҰ324326 in Mitspah to meet with the \add вүҲBabylonians\add* who came to us. \add вүҲSoВҰ324324\add* harvest wine, summerВҰ324337 fruitВҰ324337, and oilВҰ324338 and store them in your containers. Live in the citiesВҰ324342 thatВҰ324343 you've \add вүҲoccupied\add*.вҖқ
\v 11 ThenВҰ324347 all the Judeans in Moav, amongВҰ324355 the people of AmmonВҰ324357, and in EdomВҰ324358, and in every land heardВҰ324363 that the Babylonian kingВҰ324367 had allowed a \add вүҲsmall number of people\add* to stay in YehudahВҰ324371, and that he'd appointedВҰ324373 GedalyahВҰ324377 (son of AhikamВҰ324380, son of ShafanВҰ324383) over them.
\v 12 \add вүҲSoВҰ324385\add* all the Judeans from every placeВҰ324391 that they'd be drivenВҰ324393 into, cameВҰ324396 \add back\add* to YehudahВҰ324399 to GedalyahВҰ324402 at Mitspah, and they \add вүҲharvested a lot\add* of wine and summerВҰ324406 fruitВҰ324406.
\s1 The murder of Gedalyah
\rem /s1 Gedaliah Is Murdered; A Plot against Gedaliah
\s4 Southern kingdom
\r (2 Kgs 25:25-26)
\p
\v 13 \add Some time later,\add* Kareah'sВҰ324414 son Yonatan and all the army commandersВҰ324417 from the countrysideВҰ324420, cameВҰ324421 to GedalyahВҰ324424 at Mitspah,
\v 14 andВҰ324427 \add вүҲasked\add* him, вҖңDo you realise that the Ammonite KingВҰ324435 BaalisВҰ324433 has sentВҰ324439 Netanyah's son YishmaelВҰ324442 to \add вүҲassassinate\add* you?вҖқ \add вүҲHowever\add* Ahikim's son GedaliahВҰ324452 didn'tВҰ324448 believeВҰ324450 them
\v 15 \add вүҲso\add* Kareah'sВҰ324460 son Yohanan spoke privately to GedalyahВҰ324464 at Mitspah, вҖңAllow me to goВҰ324468 \add and\add* kill Netanyah's YishmaelВҰ324473. No one will suspect me. Why shouldВҰ324468 he kill you? Why allow all of YehudahВҰ324486 that has been gatheredВҰ324487 to you to be scatteredВҰ324483 and the remnantВҰ324490 destroyed?вҖқ
\p
\v 16 \add вүҲHowever\add* Ahikam'sВҰ324497 son GedalyahВҰ324494 \add вүҲreplied\add* to Kareah'sВҰ324503 son YohananВҰ324500, вҖң\add No,\add* don'tВҰ324504 do that, becauseВҰ324512 you'reВҰ324515 lying about YishmaelВҰ324519.вҖқ
\c 41
\rem /s1 Insurrection against Gedaliah; The Murder of Gedaliah
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲHowever,\add* in the seventhВҰ324525 monthВҰ324524, YishmaelВҰ324527 (son of Netanyah, son of Elishama from the royalВҰ324535 family) and some officers of the kingВҰ324537 cameвҖ”he had ten menВҰ324539 with him. \add вүЎThey came\add* to Ahikam'sВҰ324546 son GedalyahВҰ324543 at Mitspah and \add вүҲhad a meal\add* togetherВҰ324551.\x + \xo 41:1-3: \xt 2Ki 25:25.\x*
\v 2 ThenВҰ324554 Yishmael and the tenВҰ324559 menВҰ324560 who were with him, \add вүҲstood\add* up and attacked with their swordsВҰ324576. Yishmael killedВҰ324577 GedalyahВҰ324569, who the Babylonian kingВҰ324582 had put in charge of the \add вүҲregion\add*,
\v 3 andВҰ324587 they killed all the Judeans who were with GedalyahВҰ324597 \add there\add* at Mitspah, as well as the Babylonian soldiers who were there.
\p
\v 4 The \add вүҲnext\add* dayВҰ324613 \add вүҲbefore anyoneВҰ324619 found out that GedalyahВҰ324618 had been murdered\add*,
\v 5 eightyВҰ324628 menВҰ324624 from Shekem, ShilohВҰ324626, andВҰ324623 from ShomronВҰ324627 cameВҰ324623 who had shavedВҰ324630 off their beardsВҰ324631, torn their clothesВҰ324633, and cutВҰ324634 themselvesВҰ324634 \add in mourning\add*. They were carrying grain offerings and incense to \add вүҲbe offered at\add* Yahweh'sВҰ324640 \add вүҲresidence\add*.
\v 6 Netanyah's son YishmaelВҰ324643 went out of Mitspah to meet them, weepingВҰ324653 as he went. \add вүҲWhenВҰ324642 he reached\add* them, he told them to comeВҰ324659 andВҰ324642 see what had happened to Ahikam'sВҰ324665 son GedalyahВҰ324662.
\v 7 ThenВҰ324678 as theyВҰ324669 \add вүҲreached\add* the middle of the townВҰ324673, YishmaelВҰ324675 and his menВҰ324684 slaughteredВҰ324674 them \add and threw their bodies\add* into a cisternВҰ324682.
\p
\v 8 \add вүҲHowever,\add* tenВҰ324689 of them \add вүҲbargained with YishmaelВҰ324697 about some\add* wheatВҰ324708, barleyВҰ324709, oilВҰ324710, andВҰ324689 honeyВҰ324711 \add вүҲthat they'd left out\add* in the countrysideВҰ324707, \add вүҲso\add* he didn'tВҰ324698 killВҰ324700 them along with the others.
\v 9 The \add water storage\add* cisternВҰ324718 when Yishmael had thrown all the bodies of thoseВҰ324750 he'd killed \add ?вүҲincluding\add* GedalyahВҰ324733, had been dug by King AsaВҰ324738 \add вүҲin defence against\add* Yisrael's King BaashaВҰ324740. \add вүҲNow\add* Netanyah's son Yishmael had filledВҰ324745 it \add вүҲwith dead bodies\add*.
\v 10 Next Yishmael captured the remainingВҰ324772 people in Mitspah, \add вүҲincludingВҰ324767\add* the king's daughtersВҰ324765 andВҰ324752 all the others who the chiefВҰ324777 bodyguardВҰ324779 Nevuzar-Adan had assigned to Ahikam'sВҰ324785 son GedalyahВҰ324782. \add вүҲSoВҰ324752\add* Netanyah's son Yishmael captured them to hand over to the \add вүҲAmmonites\add*.
\p
\v 11 \add вүҲMeanwhile\add* Kareah'sВҰ324803 son YohananВҰ324800 and all the army commandersВҰ324806 with him, heard about all the evilВҰ324813 \add >things\add* thatВҰ324814 Netanyah's son YishmaelВҰ324816 had doneВҰ324815,
\v 12 \add вүҲso\add* they tookВҰ324821 all their menВҰ324826 to fight against YishmaelВҰ324831. They \add вүҲcame across\add* him at the largeВҰ324840 pool \add вүҲnear\add* Giv'on \add city\add*
\v 13 \add вүҲWhenВҰ324844\add* all the peopleВҰ324848 who'd \add вүҲbeen captured by\add* YishmaelВҰ324852 sawВҰ324845 YohananВҰ324855 andВҰ324844 all the army commandersВҰ324862 theyВҰ324866 were \add вүҲvery relieved\add*.
\v 14 \add вүҲSoВҰ324868\add* all \add &those\add* peopleВҰ324871 thatВҰ324872 YishmaelВҰ324875 had captured \add вүҲwere freed\add* andВҰ324868 wentВҰ324880 \add вүҲback\add* with Kareah'sВҰ324886 son YohananВҰ324883.
\v 15 \add вүҲUnfortunately,\add* Netanyah's son YishmaelВҰ324888 escapedВҰ324892 from YohananВҰ324896, along with eightВҰ324893 of his menВҰ324894, andВҰ324897 they wentВҰ324897 to the Ammonites.
\rem /s1 Flight to Egypt
\p
\v 16 Then Kareah'sВҰ324908 son YohananВҰ324905 and all the army commandersВҰ324911 with him, took all the peopleВҰ324920 from Mitspah who'd been \add вүҲrescued\add* from Netanyah's son YishmaelВҰ324924 afterВҰ324931 he'd killed Ahikam'sВҰ324938 son GedalyahВҰ324935. \add вүЎThey took\add* \add &those\add* warriorsВҰ324939, and womenВҰ324942 and children and court-officials thatВҰ324921 they'd \add вүҲsaved at Giv'on\add*,
\v 17 and wentВҰ324949 and stayed at GerutВҰ324951-Kimham near Beyt-Lehem, \add вүҲgetting ready\add* to go to EgyptВҰ324961
\v 18 because of the \add вүҲBabylonians\add*. (They \add вүҲworried about theirВҰ324967 response\add* because Netanyah's son YishmaelВҰ324971 had \add вүҲassassinated\add* Ahikam'sВҰ324980 son GedalyahВҰ324977 who'd been appointedВҰ324983 in the \add вүҲregion\add* by the Babylonian kingВҰ324984.)
\c 42
\s1 The people ask Yirmeyah to pray
\rem /s1 The People Ask Jeremiah to Pray for Them; Warning to Stay in Judah; Jeremiah Advises Survivors Not to Migrate
\p
\v 1 Then all the army commandersВҰ324993, as well as Kareah'sВҰ324998 son YohananВҰ324995, Hoshayah'sВҰ325002 son YezanyahВҰ324999, and all the peopleВҰ325005 from the less \add вүҲprominent\add* to the \add вүҲmost important officials\add* approachedВҰ324990 the prophet Yirmeyah
\v 2 andВҰ325011 \add вүҲasked\add* him, вҖңPlease \add вүҲlisten to our request\add*. \add вүЎPlease\add* ask your godВҰ325026 YahwehВҰ325025 our on behalf of \add вүҲall of us who are left here, becauseВҰ325032 there's not very many of us left as you can see\add*.
\v 3 Ask your godВҰ325046 YahwehВҰ325045 to tell us what we should doВҰ325058 and where we should goВҰ325051.вҖқ
\p
\v 4 вҖң\add Sure,\add* I'veВҰ325064 heardВҰ325064 \add your concerns\add*,вҖқ the prophetВҰ325063 Yirmeyah \add вүҲrespondedВҰ325060\add*. вҖңListen, Ill pray to your godВҰ325070 Yahweh as you've all requested. Whatever Yahweh answersВҰ325078, I'll tell you. I'll keep nothing back from you all.вҖқ
\p
\v 5 вҮ”вҖңWe \add promise\add* to do everythingВҰ325103 thatВҰ325106 your godВҰ325109 Yahweh tells us to do,вҖқ they told Yirmeyah. вҖңIf we don'tВҰ325102, thenВҰ325089 Yahweh can be a true andВҰ325089 faithfulВҰ325099 witnessВҰ325097 against us.
\v 6 WhetherВҰ325114 it's good or bad, we'll obey the \add вүҲinstructions from\add* our god YahwehВҰ325122 who we're \add вүҲasking you to speak\add* to, so that it may be well with us when we obey \add *his\add* \add вүҲresponse\add*.вҖқ
\s1 The answer of Master of praying for Yirmeyah
\rem /s1 The Lord's Answer to Jeremiah's Prayer
\p
\v 7 After tenВҰ325145 daysВҰ325146, Yahweh'sВҰ325150 \add вүҲresponse\add* came to Yirmeyah,
\v 8 \add вүҲso\add* \add *he\add* calledВҰ325155 Kareah'sВҰ325161 son YohananВҰ325158 andВҰ325155 all the army commandersВҰ325165, as well as all the peopleВҰ325171 from the less \add вүҲprominent\add* to the \add вүҲmost important officials\add*,
\v 9 thenВҰ325177 he told them, вҖңYou all sentВҰ325186 me to Yisrael's godВҰ325183 YahwehВҰ325182 \add вүҲto pass on your requests\add* \add вүҲandВҰ325177 here's his reply\add*:
\v 10 If you all stay in this \add вүҲregion\add*, then I'll buildВҰ325199 you up and not tear you down. I'll plantВҰ325203 you and not pull you all out, becauseВҰ325207 I'm upset about the harm thatВҰ325212 I'veВҰ325213 doneВҰ325213 to you all.
\v 11 Don't be afraid of the Babylonian kingВҰ325220 \add вүҲany more\add*. This is Yahweh'sВҰ325233 declaration: Don't be afraid of himВҰ325226 becauseВҰ325234 I'm with you all to saveВҰ325238 you and to rescueВҰ325240 you from hisВҰ325226 \add вүҲclutches\add*,
\v 12 because I'll giveВҰ325244 you all mercy. I'll have compassionВҰ325247 on you, andВҰ325244 I'll restoreВҰ325249 you all back to your \add вүҲcountry\add*.
\p
\v 13 \add вүҲHowever,\add* suppose that you all decide not to listenВҰ325264 to the \add вүҲwords\add* of your godВҰ325267 YahwehВҰ325266, andВҰ325255 \add вүҲdecide\add* not to stay in this \add вүҲregion\add*,
\v 14 \add and\add* if you all sayВҰ325269 that you'll goВҰ325274 to EgyptВҰ325273 \add (Heb. Mitsrayim)\add* to live there whereВҰ325275 there's no war, and no trumpetsВҰ325281 \add вүҲsignalling\add*, and no \add вүҲshortage of\add* foodВҰ325284,
\v 15 Now \add you\add* \add вүҲremaining people\add* listenВҰ325293 to Yahweh'sВҰ325296 messageВҰ325294: Yisrael's godВҰ325304, Commander-in-chief Yahweh says that if you all \add вүҲdo decide\add* to go \add вүҲandВҰ325291 stay\add* \add down\add* in EgyptВҰ325313,
\v 16 then the \add вүҲwar\add* that you all fear will overtakeВҰ325325 you in Egypt. The famineВҰ325329 that you're anxiousВҰ325334 about will follow you all to Egypt, andВҰ325318 then you'll dieВҰ325341 there,
\v 17 \add вүҲi.e.,\add* \add вүҲanyone who decides\add* to goВҰ325353 to \add вүҲlive as foreigners\add* in EgyptВҰ325354, will dieВҰ325357 from \add вүҲwar\add*, famineВҰ325359, or \add вүҲdeadly diseases\add*. There won'tВҰ325361 be any survivorsВҰ325365 from the \add #calamities\add* thatВҰ325369 I'd \add вүҲsend\add* onto them.
\p
\v 18 \add вүҲYes,\add* Yisrael's god, Commander-in-chief YahwehВҰ325378 says this: Just as my anger and rage was poured out on Yerushalem'sВҰ325389 inhabitantsВҰ325388, in the same way my anger would be poured out on all of you if you go to EgyptВҰ325395. You'd become an object of cursing and a horrorВҰ325398, \add вүҲsomething to be used as a curse word\add*, and something dishonourable, and you'd never see this placeВҰ325407 againВҰ325404.
\p
\v 19 \add Then Yirmeyah continued:\add* YahwehВҰ325411 has spokenВҰ325410 to you all, the \add вүҲremaining people\add* of YehudahВҰ325414. Don'tВҰ325415 goВҰ325417 \add down\add* to EgyptВҰ325418 as you know that I'veВҰ325423 definitely warnedВҰ325423 you all \add against that\add* today.
\v 20 \add вүҲYes,\add* you \add вүҲmade a life and death mistake\add* when you sent me to your god YahwehВҰ325439, and \add вүҲasked me to ask him for instructions for you\add* and when you all said that you'd do everything that \add *he\add* says,
\v 21 because I'veВҰ325459 reported \add >all that\add* to you today. \add вүҲHowever,\add* you haven't listenedВҰ325463 to your godВҰ325466 Yahweh'sВҰ325465 message, or to anything that he sentВҰ325470 me \add to tell\add* you all about.
\v 22 \add вүҲSoВҰ325473\add* now, you should definitely \add вүҲbe aware\add* that you'll dieВҰ325480 from \add вүҲwar\add*, famineВҰ325478, and \add вүҲdeadly diseases\add* whereВҰ325482 you all wanted to goВҰ325484 and \add вүҲlive as foreigners\add*.
\c 43
\s1 Yirmeyah gets taken to Egypt
\rem /s1 Taken to Egypt, Jeremiah Warns of Judgment; Jeremiah Taken to Egypt; Jeremiah Is Taken to Egypt
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲWhen\add* Yirmeyah had finishedВҰ325490 \add вүҲpassing on\add* Yahweh'sВҰ325503 messages thatВҰ325505 their god Yahweh had told him to say,
\v 2 Hoshayah'sВҰ325521 son AzaryahВҰ325518, Kareah'sВҰ325525 son YohananВҰ325522, and all the arrogantВҰ325529 men told Yirmeyah, вҖңYou're \add вүҲlying\add* \add to us\add*. Our godВҰ325540 YahwehВҰ325539 didn'tВҰ325537 send you to \add вүҲtell us\add* not to goВҰ325544 \add and\add* live in EgyptВҰ325545.
\v 3 \add It's\add* because Neriyah's son Baruk is incitingВҰ325554 youВҰ325555 againstВҰ325556 us \add so that\add* we'll \add stay here and\add* \add вүҲget captured by the Babylonians\add* to be \add either\add* put to deathВҰ325563 or be taken as exilesВҰ325565 to BabylonВҰ325567.вҖқ
\p
\v 4 \add вүҲSoВҰ325569\add* Kareah'sВҰ325575 son YohananВҰ325572, all the army officers, andВҰ325569 all \add the rest of\add* the peopleВҰ325582, refused to \add вүҲtake notice of Yahweh'sВҰ325584 instructions\add* to \add remainВҰ325585\add* living in the YehudahВҰ325587 \add вүҲregionВҰ325586\add*.
\v 5 \x + \xo 43:5-7: \xt 2Ki 25:26.\x*в—ҷ
